title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain. Cream the eggs and butter. Add spinach and rest of dry ingredients.
Mix and chill 1/2 hour. Shape into balls. Grease cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Bake chicken at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain off broth.
Pour spaghetti sauce and mushrooms over chicken; put back into oven for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and melt.
Ready to serve with mashed potatoes.

title: marvelous carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an electric mixer bowl combine carrots, eggs, sugar and oil.
Beat until well mixed.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into 2 oiled and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool layers.
Frost.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces.
Boil 3 minutes or until tender.
Drain; add onion, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole.
Mix butter and crumbs; sprinkle over squash.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger stuffed bread
directions: Brown hamburger; add vegetables and cook until tender; drain. Stir in cheese soup, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Slice off top of bread loaf; hollow out center.
Reserve bread from center of loaf; tear into small cubes.
Stir bread cubes into meat mixture.
Spoon mixture into hollowed loaf; cut cheese slices diagonally.
Arrange on top of loaf; place top of bread atop cheese slices.
Wrap in foil and heat at 350° about 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chili(real hot!)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil. Add ground beef and stir until meat changes color.
Add all other ingredients and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Eat as is or serve over prepared Uncle Ben's wild rice mix.

title: oven browned potatoes
directions: Heat in saucepan to melt, enough bacon grease to coat cubed potatoes.
Put potato cubes in a large bowl.
Pour enough warm (not hot) bacon grease over potato cubes to coat.
With a slotted spoon or strainer, put potatoes on sprayed baking sheet, letting extra grease drip off.
Lightly sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 425° oven for 1 hour, or until done.
Once in a while, stir potatoes around to brown on all sides.

title: pineapple and cheese casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, flour, cheese and sugar together.
Grease casserole bowl.
Put in mix.
Crush crackers over top of pineapple.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: grandma ada's orange rolls(yields 24 rolls)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
With electric mixer add 1/4 cup of the sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and 6 tablespoons melted butter to the yeast mixture.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Knead in rest of flour.
Let rise until doubled, 2 to 3 hours.
Knead until smooth 1 minute.
Divide dough in half. Roll 1/2 of dough into a 12-inch circle.
Combine remaining 3/4 cup sugar and orange rind.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle with 1/2 of sugar mix.
Cut 12 pie shaped pieces. Roll from wide end to point, forming a crescent.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place point side down in rows in a large rectangular pan.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Pour warm topping over immediately.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in tight covered jar.
To serve: Add 2 teaspoons to a cup of boiling water and serve with a slice of lemon.

title: cheese topped buns
directions: In a small bowl, stir together butter or margarine, cheese and basil.
Spread on split buns.
Place on the rack of an unheated broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until toasted.
Serves 6.

title: peach-pear jam
directions: Peel, core and grind or chop fruit.
Measure 2 cups of each. Combine all ingredients in a large kettle.
Bring to a full, rolling boil.
Boil hard, uncovered, for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Pour at once into hot, sterilized jars; seal.
Makes 7 half pints.

title: hamburger corn bake
directions: Place oil in skillet.
Add meat and break it up and brown it. Add green pepper, onion, salt, corn and tomatoes.
Pour meat-vegetable mixture into a 9 x 13-inch rectangular casserole dish.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar; stir in warm beer.
Spoon into greased bread pans.
Do not let rise.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tuna 'n rice dinner
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add onion; cook and stir until tender but not browned.
Stir in vegetables, milk, soup and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Stir in tuna, rice and parsley; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Stir.
Garnish with almonds (if desired).
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma's breakfast muffins
directions: Put dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add milk until dough is neither too thick or too thin.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil. As they brown, they will come to the top of the oil.
Brown to a golden brown, turning over and browning other side.
Then enjoy with syrup.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix hot water and oats and allow to stand.
Sift flour, cinnamon and salt.
Cream together shortening and sugars; beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add oats mix and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: my grandma's coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream fats together and add sugar gradually, add beaten eggs and mix well.
Add coconut and mix.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together, gradually stir into cookie dough then stir in the oats and vanilla.
Roll in the size of walnuts and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: potatoes soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large stock pot.
Add broth and potatoes, parsley, garlic and cook till potatoes are tender.
Make roux out of milk and flour and add to soup to thicken as desired.

title: ms. dollie's dumplings
directions: Beat egg and fill cup with sweet milk.
Roll dumplings out; cut and let stand 1 hour.
Drop into boiling chicken broth.
By the time you get them all in, they are probably done.
Dough may be refrigerated overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Either pour over or on meat or baste meat with mixture.

title: aunt ola's oven baked stew
directions: Season meat with salt.
Arrange meat and vegetables in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour tomatoes and consomme over meat mixture and sprinkle tapioca on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours or all day.
You can not overcook, since the longer it cooks the better it tastes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half and pound the pieces between sheets of plastic wrap until they are 1/4 inch thick.
Blend the parsley, chives, salt and pepper and set aside.
Divide the butter into 8 pieces.
Roll each piece in herb mixture.
Place a butter ball in the center of each chicken piece and roll each one up in such a way that the butter is completely enclosed.
Secure the rolls with a toothpick.
Dust the rolls with flour.
Dip them in beaten eggs and roll them in the bread crumbs.
Deep fry the chicken in medium-hot oil until golden brown, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve with shoestring potatoes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: frozen coleslaw
directions: Cover all with salad dressing.
Top with small pieces of cheese.
Cover bowl; chill 24 hours.
Toss or leave in layers; serve.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil fryer with onion, salt, and pepper.
When done debone and cook spaghetti in the broth.
Add Velveeta cheese and oleo and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Mix well and pour into large casserole dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
Let stand for at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mixture will be very thin.
Place peanut butter balls in one at a time and roll with spoon.
Place on wax paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish, starting with drained, cooked hamburger.
Next layer is Tater Tots, then put cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sleepy hollow hot spiced cider
directions: Combine cider, bay leaves, cinnamon sticks and cloves in large saucepan.
Place over medium-low heat; simmer for at least 30 minutes (do not boil).
Pour cider into heated mugs (do not strain) and serve immediately.

title: cookie's kiss pudding for six
directions: Separate yellows from whites of eggs.
Beat yellows, sugar and flour together.
Then add milk.
Cook slowly until pudding comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Remove from heat. Add meringue made from egg whites.
Bake long enough to brown the meringue.

title: the best cheesecake
directions: In small bowl with mixer at low speed, beat butter or margarine, flour, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 egg yolk and 1/2 of grated peel until well mixed; shape into ball; wrap; chill 1 hour.

title: greek-style beans and lamb
directions: Soak beans, drain and rinse.
Add 6 cups fresh water; cover and simmer about 1 hour or until nearly tender.
Drain.
In Dutch oven or heavy kettle, saute onion in olive oil.
Add lamb and brown on all sides.
Add beans, 1 1/4 cups water and seasonings. Simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add tomatoes and 1/4 cup chopped parsley.
Additional water may be added, if necessary.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes longer or until beans and lamb are tender.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; garnish with additional chopped parsley.
Serves 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, combine apples, nuts, raisins and sugar.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs; stir in oil and vanilla and add to apple mixture. Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; mix well.
Gently stir dry ingredients into apple mixture.
Pour into greased dish; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of square baking pan.
Combine Bisquick, sugar and milk.
Pour over oleo.
Add berries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low calorie rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put sugar-free pudding (dry) with other ingredients.
Stir over low heat until thickened.
Can add raisins.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Heat milk; mix in sugar, flour and eggs.
Add mixture to corn.
Add vanilla and pour in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: parker house rolls(takes sixty minutes)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease your pans.
Roll out mixture; cut with a glass.
Fold over with a pat of butter in it. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar for 7 minutes at high speed.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flavoring, flour and milk.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: no guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 9-inch pie plate, mix soup, vegetables and chicken. Mix milk, egg and baking mix. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: easy italian vegetables
directions: Preheat grill to medium - high or oven to 450°F.
Center vegetables on aluminum foil.
Spoon salad dressing over vegetables.
Fold foil over vegetables to make a packet.
Grill 14 - 16 min. or bake 35 - 40 min.

title: raspberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Partially jell.
Blend in the sour cream.
Add pie filling.
Let chill several hours.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, stir in frozen raspberries until thawed and separated.
Add bananas, pineapple and nuts. Pour into a 9 by 13 inch pan.
Let set.

title: "kolyva" (sitari) - boiled wheat with sweets
directions: Sort and wash wheat.
In large pot, boil wheat with 2 tablespoons salt for 3 hours or until tender.
Drain and rinse well in cold water.
Spread wheat out on a large tablecloth to absorb excess moisture.

title: spanish corn with fish sticks
directions: In a skillet, saut the onion and peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in the flour, salt, pepper and sugar until blended. Add tomatoes and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring until thickened.
Stir in corn.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease.
Spread over bottom of pan or casserole dish.
Mix pepper, onions, celery, soup, rice and water together and pour on top of sausage.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix by hand and chill 1 hour.

title: angels kiss
directions: Add all ingredients into blender or smoothie maker.
Blend together.
(Great with Mexican dishes.)
Serves 1.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix jello and let cool slightly.
Add in pineapple.
Slice bananas lengthwise and place in jello.
Chill until firm.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Layer half the eggplant, tomatoes, peppers, onions, salt, pepper, oil, and all the bread crumbs in a greased shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients. Sprinkle with tapioca.
Bake at 350° covered with foil for 1 hour. Top with cheese.
Bake again until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa casserole
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1/4-inch slices.
Mix remainder of ingredients together.
Pour mixture first into 2-liter size casserole dish.
Layer kielbasa on top in carpet-like fashion. Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and applesauce.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to the applesauce mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: tomato-cucumber relish
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper; add tomato, cucumber and onion.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Before serving, drain well.
Stir in sweet pickle.

title: new york fire department cheese cake
directions: Combine ingredients, except the pie filling.
Mix until smooth and pour into an 11 x 7-inch pan. Bake 1 hour in a preheated 375° oven. Cool completely before covering top with filling.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust; refrigerate until ready to use.
Heat oven to 400°.
Beat egg slightly.
Add sugar, sour cream, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add apples; mix until blended.
Put into crust. Bake for 30 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Mix other ingredients; sprinkle over pie.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey, wheat germ and dry milk; mix well.
Stir in raisins.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut, coating well.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: party snack mix (diabetic)
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Combine cereals in large bowl. Pour mixture over and toss well.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Toss well.
Bake 45 minutes in large shallow baking dish.
Stir occasionally.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container. Yields 9 cups.
Serving size, 1/2 cup.
Per serving:
calories 125, carbohydrate 169, protein 19, fat 69, sodium 476 (use optional less sodium).
Exchange per serving:
1 starch/bread and 1 fat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour,
stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool completely.
Break apart.
Makes about 5 quarts caramel corn.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°; cool thoroughly.
Mix together with mixer the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add strawberries.
When berries have thawed and jello begins to thicken, pour over cream cheese mixture.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, buttermilk, sugar and vanilla and beat well with mixer.
Add pineapple, carrots, coconut, walnuts, soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn out immediately onto cooling rack.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting when completely cooled.

title: squash ball
directions: Cook squash, onion, salt and pepper until done.
Drain off liquid.
Add egg and flour and drop by teaspoonful into hot grease.

title: cinnamon pull aparts
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Melt together margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour on top of rolls.
Cover with Saran Wrap (spray with Pam).
Leave out overnight.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before turning over onto the plate.

title: turkey goulash
directions: Bring all liquid to a boil.
Add macaroni; cook about 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all together.
If too hot, add more tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly. With fork, add sugar, stirring until dissolved. Stir in caramel topping and butter; mix well. Stir in pecan halves. Pour filling into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and serve.

title: chili (mexico)
directions: Brown beef in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cream cheese candy
directions: Melt cream cheese in double boiler.
Mix in sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto large sheet of waxed paper. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Bake skinless chicken breasts, lightly seasoned with pepper, garlic and oregano.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, combine the sour cream, soups, green chilies and spices.
Heat on medium heat, stirring occasionally.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: Mix ingredients well in a jumbo canister or other large container and chill until ready to serve.
Great punch for showers, weddings, etc.

title: todd's lower fat hamburgers
directions: Mix turkey and beef together.
Add in soup mix, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Make into patties.
Broil or grill. This tastes best if you can let it set overnight, so flavors are released.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In large bowl mix rice, celery, onion, chestnuts, almonds, mayonnaise, soup, flavor enhancer, corn oil, adding chicken last, stir gently.
Spoon into 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Mix together Ritz crackers and margarine and sprinkle over top of chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jean d's peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt sugar and butter with milk over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When it comes to a boil, boil 5 minutes.
Continue stirring.
Then remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix well and pour into buttered pan and chill.

title: cream tomato soup
directions: Saut onion in margarine in large saucepan until tender.
Add flour, salt and pepper and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and tomato juice; cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add bay leaf; simmer 1 minute.

title: pumpkin dessert ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 2-quart ring mold.
Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, water, nuts, raisins and pumpkin.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed; scrape bowl constantly. Add egg; beat 2 more minutes, scraping.
Pour into prepared mold. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with lemon sauce or whipped cream.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Place vegetables in boiling water; cover and boil for about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients with 1/4 cup water in saucepan. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp; mix well.
Simmer until thick, stirring constantly. Fold in shrimp.
Heat to serving temperature.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: squash cakes
directions: Wash squash and boil until tender.
Drain and mash squash. Add onion, egg, flour and salt and pepper.
Press into cakes by hand.
Fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 25 minutes.
Cook on 350°.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening and add brown sugar; stir until mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts and chocolate chips.

title: sausage and gravy
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until done. Remove to paper towel. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings. Add the flour and stir with whisk until brown in color. Slowly whisk in the milk and coffee. Cook until desired thickness. Season with salt and pepper. Serve over biscuits while hot. Yield: 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.
Spread tomato catsup on top before serving.

title: derek's yogurt
directions: Empty one can condensed milk into a pitcher.
Add 1 1/2 cans boiling water (use potholder!).
Stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cans cold milk.
Allow to cool down slightly, then add 4 ounces yogurt. Whisk until smooth.
Pour into baby food jars (I use eight 6-ounce jars).
Cover jars and sit them in roasting pan filled with cold water.
Place in warm oven (on lowest setting).
After 40 minutes, turn oven off but leave yogurt in until oven is completely cold.
(I make this in the evening and leave them in overnight.)
Once oven is cold, place yogurt in refrigerator.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is evaporated.
Chill. Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add soda, salt and flour. Fold in raisins.
Roll in balls and dip in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: sweet gherkins
directions: Cover fresh cucumbers with hot brine made by dissolving 2 cups salt in 2 1/2 qts. boiling water.
Soak cucumbers in brime for 24 hours.
Drain.

title: peppermint ice cream dessert
directions: Combine melted oleo, sugar and graham crackers.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together oleo and chocolate.
Beat in eggs and powdered sugar.
Put over first layer and freeze two hours. Spread ice cream on second layer and refreeze.
Spread on Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate shavings.
Refreeze.

title: sunny holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Garnish as desired. Makes 3 quarts.

title: buttered green beans
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Bring water to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Add beans; cover, reduce heat to medium and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain and toss beans with butter.
Yields 6 servings.

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Then blend in egg, mixing well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour into pans and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; chop the green onions and dice the water chestnuts.
Set aside.
Combine the sour cream, mayonnaise and soup mix.
Mix well and then add the spinach, onions and water chestnuts.
Cut out top of loaves of bread and fill with mixture. (This will fill two loaves of bread or just refill one.)
Great for large groups.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine the chicken, soup, mayonnaise and macaroni; mix well and spread mixture into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until cooked through.

title: pico de gallo (relish)
directions: Chop cilantro in container.
Add the chopped/diced ingredients.
Mix together well.
Squeeze the lemon over the top and mix well again.
Add salt to taste.

title: john's olde timey granola
directions: Mix together wheat germ and milk.
Set aside.
Stir into the oats, nuts, soy beans, bran, almonds and pecan pieces the wheat germ and milk and then the following ingredients:
soy bean oil, honey, vanilla, allspice and nutmeg.

Pour mixture into well-Pammed 2-inch deep baking dish, 10 by 15-inch or two smaller ones and bake in moderate oven (I use 250°, but my oven may run a little hot) for about 1 hour and 20 minutes or until deep golden brown, thoroughly stirring at least twice to prevent some parts from overheating.
After cooling, mix in raisins and chopped dates.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
In pan, bring to boil margarine, Crisco, water and cocoa.
Remove from stove; stir in flour, sugar and salt.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs. Pour into a 9 x 11-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and ice while warm.
Mix this cake by hand.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large stainless pan.
Mix and set overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Bring to a boil and add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer for about 30 minutes until thick and dry.
Seal in hot jars.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add the egg and mix well. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pat onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Spread with chocolate frosting when cooled.

title: chicken cheese potatoes
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, sour cream, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Heat until it is a creamy sauce.
In casserole dish, layer the potatoes, cheese, chicken and top with sauce.
Bake for about an hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir
together	all
ingredients
and put in casserole. Crush 1
roll
of
Ritz crackers; mix with 1 stick margarine. Top casserole with cracker crumb mixture and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 8 x 14-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudgie scotch squares
directions: Mix bits and crumbs.
Add milk and mix well.
Stir in nuts. Grease a large cake pan (9 x 13-inch) and add mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool 45 minutes before cutting.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 3 minutes; drain. Saute bacon in large saucepan until golden.
Remove all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add onion and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups of milk, scraping sides and bottom of pan.
Add potatoes and clam juice.
Heat to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter, pinch of thyme, flour, 1 cup milk and cream.
Heat to boiling, then simmer until thickened (5 to 10 minutes).
Stir in clams and simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: easy snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Store in an airtight container.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: spinach empire
directions: Preheat oven to 180°C.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well.
Place spinach, bread crumbs, onion, egg, melted margarine, cheese, garlic, thyme, pepper and salt in a medium bowl.
Arrange tomato slices in a shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Spoon 1/4 spinach mixture onto each tomato slice.
Shape into a dome.
Bake in preheated oven 15 minutes or until set and heated.
Serve.

title: simple pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, until light.
Add corn syrup, butter, and vanilla extract.
Fold in pecans.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: aunt jane's chicken in foil(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put small amount of butter or margarine in nonstick skillet; melt over medium heat.
Add carrots and celery; saute until tender.
Add mushrooms; stir.
Remove from heat.
Take a piece of foil large enough to wrap 1 chicken breast along with 1/4 of vegetable mixture.
Coat bottom of foil slightly with margarine; add 1/4 of rice, then 1/4 vegetables and then place chicken breast on top.
Seal the ends of foil.
Do this with all the rice, vegetables and chicken breasts.
Place on a cookie sheet in hot oven for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Careful when opening pouches.
You can also add any spices to chicken you desire!

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Dredge shrimp in flour and set aside.
In 9 inch skillet heat oil; add garlic and saute until golden.
Add shrimp to skillet and saute, turning occasionally until shrimp begin to turn pink (about 3 minutes).
Add wine and bring to boil; cook about 1 minute. Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper and remove from heat. Garnish with parsley and lemon slices.
Serves two.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Combine milk, water and butter in saucepan; cook over low heat until butter melts (do not overheat). Gradually add liquid mixture to dry mixture.
Add gradually remaining flour until dough is soft.

title: sweet potato candy
directions: Cook potato until soft.
Mash good.
Add vanilla.
Start adding powdered sugar until a stiff dough forms.
Put a little powdered sugar on table to keep from sticking.
Take a little dough at a time and roll as you would a pie crust.
Spread peanut butter on it and roll up like a jelly roll.
Cool and slice in pieces.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine fruit, raisins, nuts and 1/2 cup of flour in a plastic bag.
Shake and cover well with flour.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and boil for one minute only. Remove from stove and add oats, crunchy peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper to cool.

title: low-fat spaghetti and turkey meatballs(18% calories from fat)
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients except spaghetti. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix softened margarine and 3 ounces cream cheese.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pickled yellow hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers and stick a pin several times in each one.
Pack in pint jars, along with carrot sticks, if you want them.
Add 1 teaspoon each of olive oil and salt.
The brine is made of half vinegar and half water, which is heated until it just boils.
Pour into jars and seal at once.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can Durkee onions.
Place into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap crescent rolls; separate into two rectangles.
Press together perforated cuts and cut lengthwise into 6 strips.
Place on top of casserole to form lattice top.
Bake 15 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered 3 to 5 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat milk, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on pan and flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Mix and melt together the 2 chips and peanut butter.
Pour a little less than half the mixture into a chilled jelly roll pan and spread on bottom.
Set remaining mixture aside and add 1 package of salted peanuts to the remaining mixture.
Mix together in saucepan the evaporated milk, pudding mix and butter.
Boil for 1 minute. Take off stove and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend well. Add to the first layer of chips and peanut butter and spread it out.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Spread remaining chocolate mixture with peanuts on top.
Chill again.
Cut into small squares.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks, milk and shortening. Combine flour, baking powder and sugar. Add to egg yolk mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry. Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Bake in preheated iron.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: meatless borsch
directions: Melt oleo and put all vegetables in with the tomato soup and water.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are soft, about 1 hour. Add 2 quarts water and shredded beets shoestring style and continue to cook.
Then beat together milk, egg and flour.
Add to soup and simmer for a few minutes (one or two).
Good with or without sour cream.

title: joyce's baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Top with oil or strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Top with oven fry or buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in slightly cooled gelatin and beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, oranges, pineapple, soda and pecans. Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in 3/4 of the whipped topping.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish. Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares and garnish with remaining topping.
Makes 16 to 20 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and syrup 5 minutes.
Add soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Pour over corn and bake in oven at 200° for 1 hour.
Bake in 2 roaster pans.
Stir occasionally.

title: rookie cookies
directions: Thoroughly beat eggs, sugar and maple flavoring together in large mixing bowl.
Sift flour and salt together and add to egg mixture.
Add chopped nuts, raisins and oats.
Mix well.
Fill a greased and waxed paper lined 9x12 pan 1/2 inch deep with batter. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Remove from pan, cool and cut into bars.

title: squash pie
directions: Cook
squash
in
small
amount
of water until tender. Drain off
water	and
mash.
Combine margarine, sugar, lemon extract, flour,
eggs
and
salt.
Add to squash and mix well. (May put
in blender and mix.) Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.

title: moist and easy banana cake
directions: Slice bananas into a large mixing bowl; beat until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients; beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into a well-greased, floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, until cake tests done.

title: hamburger with baked beans
directions: Cut bacon strips in small pieces and onion. Saute. Brown ground beef with the above. Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole or baking dish. Bake at 375 for 30 minutes. Dish will stay hot some time. Before serving, garnish the top with sliced bright, red tomatoes; not important but decorates the dish.

title: cranberry fruit mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add jellied cranberry sauce.
(You can also use whole cranberry sauce.)
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in 1 cup diced peeled apples and 1 cup diced peeled oranges.
Pour into
a 6 cup mold or 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill and serve.
Serves 10.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan for approximately 1 hour at 350°. Yields 1 loaf.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Mix butter, sugar and milk. Boil hard for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Grease pan and pour in.
Let cool. Cut in squares.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots
in warm water for 30 minutes.
Drain and cut into
pieces.
Cream
sugar and margarine.	Add egg, water and orange
juice.
Mix
the
dry
ingredients together.
Stir into the batter with apricots.
Pour into a 10-inch Dutch oven and let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake for 70 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped chicken
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Spread rice on bottom.
Spoon mushroom soup over top.
Lay chicken pieces on top and add water. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes (no peeking).

title: mexican mush
directions: Mix browned ground beef, pinto beans, taco sauce, and tomatoes in pan and simmer.
Mix together the following and let stand while putting together everything else:
Italian dressing, lettuce, tomatoes, onion, and celery.
Crush 1 package of Tortilla chips and set aside.
Leave 1 package whole.
Then:
add grated cheese to meat mixture.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Add salad mixture. Add crushed chips.

title: u.p. scramble
directions: Saute white onions, then scramble with the eggs.
Add cheese and venison sausage or salami.
Serve immediately.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with broccoli.
Mix cream of chicken soup and milk and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, covered.
Cover top with croutons, then with cheese. Bake uncovered about 20 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: devilish chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in square pan (8 or 9-inches) for 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not overcook as it will be dry.
Serves 4.

title: eggplant pasta
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy, large skillet over medium heat.
Add eggplant and garlic.
Cover mixture and cook until eggplant is just tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Mix in red bell pepper, mushrooms, oregano and dried red pepper and saute until mushrooms are tender, about 4 minutes.
Add wine and cook until mixture is almost dry, about 2 minutes.
Stir in tomato and olives and cook until mixture is just heated through.
Transfer sauce to large bowl.
Add pasta and pine nuts and toss well.
Serve, passing fresh grated Parmesan cheese separately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vanilla fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and pudding with a wire whisk.
Drain fruit. Stir into mixture and chill overnight.
Serve on leaf of lettuce.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In
large saucepan over low heat, melt sugar, chocolate chips and evaporated milk, stirring frequently.
Leave on low heat
and let come to full bubbling boil.
Stir constantly for 15 to
20 minutes
(mixture
is done when a few drops in cold water
forms soft
ball.)
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, margarine,
vanilla
and
nuts.
Stir vigorously until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: potato-buttermilk soup
directions: Cover potato cubes with broth; cook until tender.
Remove from heat; don't drain.
Saute onions until tender.
Melt butter in saucepan on medium-high.
Add flour; stir 2 minutes.
Slowly stir in buttermilk and cook until it thickens.
Add onions, potatoes, broth and thyme; heat to boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 6.

title: fruit compote
directions: Stir together, putting bananas and strawberries in when ready to serve.
Enjoy.
May be doubled or tripled easily for a large group.

title: shirley's peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk into a saucepan and boil to 234 degrees, using a good candy thermometer.
Take from stove and quickly add other ingredients.
Pour into lightly buttered 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 - inch pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: yeast bread
directions: *I add enough water for this when I boil my potatoes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all. Refrigerate; enjoy!!

title: banana bread
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Bake until bread springs back to the touch at 325° for 40 minutes to 1 hour. Grease and flour pans.
Makes 2 loaf pans or 4 mini loaves.

title: double-apple bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix brown sugar, applesauce, oil and egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in apple.

title: apple cider
directions: Pour cider in percolator.
Add other ingredients in basket. Perk until red hots melt.

title: hot paprika chicken
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Fry chicken in bacon fat for 10 minutes.
Remove chicken from pan.
Add onions, garlic and paprika.
Cook until onions soften slightly.
Stir in tomatoes, broth, bay leaf and hot pepper.
Add chicken and bacon.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to the gravy and cook for 5 minutes.
Spoon gravy to chicken.
Serve with boiled potatoes or egg noodles.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg
whites
and vanilla to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar;
beating
until
stiff peaks form.
Combine cracker crumbs, pecans
and baking powder; fold into meringue mixture. Spread evenly
in greased and floured 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 20	to
25	minutes.
Cool	completely.
Serve
with whipped cream.

title: chinese hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered.
Sprinkle a few chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Upon serving, sprinkle with a few more chow mein noodles.

title: amazing peanut butter cookies(no flour)
directions: Mix and form into small balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: four cheese lasagna(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with nonfat cooking spray. Brown hamburger and pour spaghetti sauce over it. Beat egg whites with cottage and Ricotta cheeses. Layer ingredients in the following order: lasagna noodles, 1/3 of Ricotta and cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 of hamburger, 1/2 pound of Mexican cheese, lasagna noodles, 1/3 of Ricotta and cottage cheese mixture, rest of hamburger, 1/2 pound of Mozzarella, lasagna noodles, rest of Ricotta and cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 pound Mexican cheese and 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 50 minutes. Let cool for a few minutes before cutting.

title: putsch's spinach salad
directions: Stem spinach, wash and dry thoroughly.
Refrigerate.
Tear spinach into small pieces, then chop into smaller pieces using a French knife on a chopping board.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Use all fresh vegetables.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil; drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole (greek mousaka)
directions: Brown meat and finely chopped onion with olive oil.
When well browned, add water, tomato paste, parsley, butter, salt and pepper and let simmer for 1 hour or more until thickened.
Peel and cut eggplants lengthwise in 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with flour and saute in olive oil until golden brown.
Add to the already cooked chopped meat, 2 tablespoon breadcrumbs and mix well.
Butter a baking dish and sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Place 1/2 of eggplant in the dish and 1/2 of meat over eggplant.
Repeat process.
Pour well beaten eggs on top evenly.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and breadcrumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients except blueberries; beat 20 to 30 seconds, leaving some lumps.
Rinse blueberries; drain and lightly flour.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Bake in paper-lined muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: tamale or hamburger pie
directions: Make brown sauce in large skillet.
Combine ground beef, sausage, onions and green pepper.
Work until meat is browned. Add brown sauce base, tomatoes, corn, raisins, olives and chili powder; mix well.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Prepare corn bread mix according to package.
Spoon over meat mixture in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until corn bread is lightly brown.

title: hot slaw
directions: Grate cabbage.
Grind onions and peppers.
Mix with mustard and mayonnaise.
Salt to taste.

title: oatmeal fudge candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Beat about 1 minute. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: chocolate marshmallow cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, and cocoa; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour, nuts, and vanilla; mix well. Pour batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. When you remove from oven, immediately put marshmallows on the hot cake. Make following icing and pour over the still warm cake.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and Cool Whip. Add pineapple, marshmallows and nuts. Stir and chill in covered 10 x 13-inch dish. Cut into squares 1 1/2 x 1 1/2 and place on lettuce leaf and top with a strawberry or a cherry. Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned slightly.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass baking dish and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together well the sugar and cornstarch, adding water a little at a time.
Cook together until thick.
While hot, add jello, salt, food coloring, then add berries.
Chill, adding topping of Cool Whip.

title: rhubarb custard bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Press into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13 pan. Mix together butter, cake mix, 1/3 cup milk and pecans. Spread half of batter on bottom of cake pan and bake for 6 minutes at 350°. Place caramels and 1/3 cup milk in dish and heat in microwave until melted, stirring frequently. Take cake out of oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on top and pour caramel mixture on that. Pour remaining cake batter on top. Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into patties.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Turn and broil 4 minutes longer.
Pour gravy over top of patties.
Warm and serve.

title: crepe
directions: Mix everything but flour until well mixed.
Slowly add flour. Heat pan and add grease.
Form a thin film over bottom of pan. Flip.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Chop veggies fine and mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let set 3 hours before serving.

title: summertime squash
directions: Boil and drain squash.
Mix onion, bell pepper, soup and sour cream in squash.
Melt margarine and add croutons.
Mix in squash mixture with 1/2 of cheese. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with remainder of cheese. Melt a little more margarine and toss 1 cup croutons and put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Can be frozen before or after baking.)

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Boil twists for 10 minutes.
Fry hamburg and onion together, drain.
Stir in spaghetti and pizza sauces, mushrooms, pepperoni, salt and twists.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese.
Put greased foil (so cheese doesn't stick) over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onions and seasonings.
Drain.
Cook macaroni and cheese by following directions on box.
Add macaroni and cheese to the beef and onions in skillet.
Heat on low for 5 minutes. Serve with a salad or vegetable.
Serves 4.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter and eggs together.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture alternately with sour milk and soda.
Mix well, then add prunes.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350°.
Cool; put together with the following filling between layers and on top and sides.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Bake in a greased pie plate in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
You may sprinkle coconut flakes before baking.

title: icing on the cake
directions: Pudding mix makes quick frosting.
Just stir milk into mix; set aside.
Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds.
Add sifted powdered sugar, then slowly stir in pudding mixture.

title: mrs. inouye's papaya cheese pie
directions: Aloha...born and raised in Hawaii...this is one of my favorite dishes too!
Reminds me of growing up in the islands, and the food I grew up with!
I make it all the time (because it's so easy...and it never fails!) and my kids love it!

title: tomatoes and okra
directions: In saucepan, heat butter.
Add onion and cook until wilted. Add sugar and stir.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice, salt and basil. Bring to boiling point; add okra.
Cover and boil gently until okra is tender.

title: wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix on low speed one minute, mix on medium speed three minutes.
Oil and flour a Bundt pan; pour in mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°; cool 15 minutes.
After removing from pan, sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Beat milk and pudding until thick. Add Cool Whip and mix. Layer graham crackers (whole) in bottom of a 9 x 13 dish. Pour in pudding mix. Layer graham crackers on top of pudding. Spread icing on top of crackers. Refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma's sauerkraut
directions: In a good size frypan, fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and saute until onion is limp.
Fork in drained sauerkraut and stir until ingredients are evenly mixed.
Adjust the flame until it is as low as possible.
Continue to cook until sauerkraut begins to brown.
Stir in caraway seed.
Try not to eat all the sauerkraut out of the pan before serving!

title: marshmallowed sweet potatoes
directions: Place half of sweet potatoes in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Dot with half of the margarine and sprinkle with half of the cinnamon.
Layer with half of the apples.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until marshmallows are golden.
Be careful, they scorch easily!
This recipe doubles well, can be prepared a day ahead if canned apples are used.
(Great if you're in a hurry.)
Is great with ham, turkey or roast beef.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple.
Beat together the sugar, eggs, butter and milk until well blended.
Stir in bread and pineapple.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk until well mixed.
Spread over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate 4 hours, until set.
Add whipped topping if desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook in large pot over medium heat until hot and cheese is melted.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer until thick.
Baste meat while broiling, braising or barbecuing.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: fricasseed raccoon
directions: Put possum in 55 gallon drum and feed for 3 weeks (vegetables, grain, etc.).
Shoot possum between the eyes (his brain is real small, but it's around there somewhere).
Scald in 140° water with hickory ashes and green pine needles.
Scrape hair with Mason jar lid.
Rub down liberally with salt and pepper.
Place roasting rack in pan.
One cup water and 1/4 cup Wild Turkey in bottom of pan. Slow cook 2 hours (medium possum); baste often.
Remove top and brown 15 minutes.
Slice and serve on sweet potatoes.
Feeds one Hillbilly or 150 to 300 city folk.

title: glazed fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place 1 quart fresh strawberries in cooled pastry shell. Crush remaining berries in medium saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch and water, blending well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add margarine.
Stir until well blended.
Strain mixture and cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: You will need a 10-inch circle plate with 1 to 2-inch sides.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Fry meat with onion; drain.
Place in a casserole dish.
Add in order (cheese, vegetables and soup mixed with water). Distribute Tater Tots evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then 1/2 hour, uncovered.

title: homestyle meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 400° and coat large roasting pan with cooking spray.
Combine first 8 ingredients and form into 1-inch balls. Place meatballs on roasting pan and bake for 15 minutes or until browned.
Gently loosen meatballs from the bottom of the pan. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Cover meatballs and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes to thicken sauce.

title: shrimp on the barbecue
directions: Place shrimp on wooden skewer sticks (about 6 per stick). Salt and pepper shrimp.
In microwave, melt butter and garlic. Dip shrimp sticks into mixture, making sure to coat each shrimp.

title: open faced chicken sandwich(serves 2)
directions: Drain pineapple; combine chicken, pickles, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Split muffins in half; toast and butter each. Spread chicken mixture on each muffin.
Top with a slice of pineapple, then shredded cheese.
Preheat oven to 300° for 10 minutes.
Place sandwiches on a cookie sheet; bake for a few minutes or until cheese has melted.

title: skillet stuffed peppers
directions: While rice is cooking, in medium skillet, brown beef until crumbly; drain.
Add onion; cook until onion is soft.
Remove from heat.
Mix in A.1., salt, pepper, tomato sauce, corn and rice. Cut tops, seeds and membranes from peppers; discard.
Fill peppers with meat and rice mixture.
In a 10-inch skillet, place peppers and carrots.
Add butter and water.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes, or until carrots are tender.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Drain grease off and add all ingredients, except cheese; mix well Add cheese and cut in small pieces.
Cook until cheese melts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: lucille's chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peter pipers fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat to boiling before pouring over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: fruit bake
directions: Use a large glass baking dish.
Drain fruit thoroughly.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Combine other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour mixture over shrimp and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Be sure to turn shrimp every 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Crumble yeast cake in bowl. Add salt, sugar, oil and water. Stir until mixed. Add flour; knead and put into greased bowl. Let rise about 1 hour. Shape into buns. Let rise another hour. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apple-cabbage slaw
directions: Discard tough outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut into quarters and core.
Cut into thin shreds with a knife or shred on a coarse grater.
In large bowl, blend mayonnaise with sugar, lemon juice, milk, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Add cabbage and mix well. Chill several hours.
Add apples just before serving.

title: baked clams
directions: Chop 2 dozen clams and simmer 5 minutes or use 3 cans minced clams in their own juice.
Chop stalks of celery, peppers and onions and simmer in 1/4 pound of butter for 5 minutes.
In a bowl, mix 1/4 box of bread crumbs, drained clams and vegetables. Add more bread crumbs and juice of clams until is like wet stuffing.
Pile into clam shell and bake at 375° to 400° for 10 minutes.
Top with paprika.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water and cook until it spins a thread. Beat egg whites.
Add 1/2 of cooked mixture to egg whites.
Return rest of mixture to stove and cook to hard crack stage.
Pour into egg mixture and beat until starts to get thick.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Can put pecan half on each piece.

title: peachy delight
directions: Mix all ingredients; spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix well again.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until casserole is no longer juicy.
Remove from oven; let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: granny's good meatballs
directions: Mix all the ingredients (including the uncooked spaghetti pieces).
Form into balls.
Brown them in a skillet.
When all are browned, add 2 cups of tomato juice, cover and cook slow for 30 minutes.

title: old-fashioned peach cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pie filling, eggs, flavoring and nuts. Blend at low speed until completely moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch or tube pan.

title: yellow squash
directions: Cook squash, onion and celery in salted water until tender. Drain and add beaten egg, cream, cheese, salt and pepper. Place in baking dish and cover with grated cheese.
Bake slowly for 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 375° until nicely browned.
This is crusty on the outside and soft on the inside.
May also be baked in greased muffin tins at 400°.

title: cheese ball(makes 2)
directions: Roll all ingredients together except walnuts.
Divide in half, then roll each ball in walnuts.
Top each with cherry.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve.

title: batter-up brownies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir to blend.
Melt shortening in a 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: irish corned beef and cabbage
directions: In a large turkey pan, place 3 briskets in bottom with spices that come with corned beef.
Add 4 inches of water in pan.
Add peeled carrots and potatoes.
Cut each cabbage into 4 pieces. Fill to top of pan with cabbage.

title: blueberry cheese cake squares
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In medium saucepan, heat 1/4 cup sugar and margarine until melted. Stir in graham cracker crumbs. Press in 9 x 13 pan.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250 degrees.
Combine cereal and pecans in 13X9 pan and set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and butter. Microwave on high 90 seconds and stir.
Microwave 30-90 seconds more or until boiling.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda and pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel shrimp; cook onion, pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: candlestick salad
directions: Wash lettuce and drain. Put lettuce leaf on salad plate. Arrange pineapple slice in center. Peel banana. Cut off ends so banana will stand. Dip banana in pineapple juice. Stand in center of pineapple ring.	Tint mayonnaise pink with maraschino cherry juice or a drop of red food coloring. Spoon dab of pink mayonnaise over top of banana.
Let drip down the side like a melting candle. For the flame, place maraschino cherry on top.

title: super chunk cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually beat into mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool and remove from sheet.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: corn dogs
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Combine corn meal, flour, salt, oregano and garlic powder.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well. Roll each wiener in small amount of flour, then dip in batter; drain off excess.
Deep-fry until golden brown.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese, salt, pepper and broccoli.
Serve with buttered croutons.

title: pound cake
directions: No salt. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: chicken strips in butter
directions: Melt butter in skillet with garlic.
Add chicken strips.
Cook until white and tender.
Add wine (optional).
Remove chicken from pan.
Pour in 1/2 can chicken broth, heat until boiling.
Mix cornstarch with remaining broth.
Pour mixture into pan and stir. Put chicken back in skillet.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes (add mushrooms if desired).
Serve over rice.

title: dutch apple bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add and beat well, eggs and
vanilla.
Combine
separately flour, soda and salt; add
dry ingredients
alternately with orange juice.
Fold in apples and walnuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan for 55 minutes, or until loaf tests done.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces.
Arrange in 9 x 9 cake pan. Pour syrup over it.
Dot with the 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cream together the 2 tablespoons butter and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake 50 or 60 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put milk and bread in pan and heat.
Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, vanilla, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Add to cooled bread and milk.
Lightly stir in apples and raisins if desired.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour until light brown.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add kidney beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix French dressing and taco hot sauce to taste and refrigerate.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Add meat mixture, broken taco chips and sauce.
Mix well.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with ripe, mashed bananas.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: popcorn tree
directions: Will need 1 styrofoam cone (12-inches high) wooden toothpicks and gumdrops.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients like potatoes.
Place a vanilla wafer in the bottom of a cupcake holder.
Fill each liner about 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with cherry or blueberry pie filling.
This is very pretty to do on the 4th of July.
Makes 24.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening gradually.
Add sugar, beating well.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Alternate flour with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold into batter. Pour batter into greased and floured pan (10-inch tube).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and remove from pan to finish cooling.
Can be put in 2 bread pans to bake.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons water to a boil.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Break bacon into small pieces.
Mix all together and add to hot diced potatoes.

title: chocolate fudge - 5 pounds
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo.
Boil 8 to 10 minutes. Stir constantly.
Place chocolate bits, vanilla and marshmallow cream in a large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over. Stir until melted.
May add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan. Cut when set.

title: punch for a bunch
directions: Combine juices and sugar.
Chill.
Pour over ice ring.
Pour ginger ale and club soda slowly down the side of bowl (to keep from having lots of foam).

title: foil dinners
directions: In small bowl, combine juice, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, bouillon and ginger; mix well.
You now need 4 large squares of heavy aluminum foil; spray them with Pam.
On each square, place 1 piece of chicken.
Divide pineapple and veggies equal; add with chicken, then divide the sauce over all.
Fold and seal aluminum very tight.
Place on hot coals.
Watch closely; turn as needed. Should cook about 1 hour.
Or, place on baking sheet in hot oven at 400° and bake for 1 hour.

title: cafe diavolo
directions: In chafing dish, heat cognac with sugar and lemon rind.
Peel orange so that skin remains in a strip 1-inch wide and about 8-inches long.
Stick orange peel with cloves.
Hold over chafing dish with fork.
Pour 2 ounces cognac over orange peel, starting from top and allow to drip into pan.
Ignite for a few moments, adding just enough additional cognac to keep flame lit.
When flame goes out, place peel in chafing dish and simmer in hot mixture 4 to 5 minutes.
Add coffee.
Blaze some cognac on top and serve in demitasse cups.
Serves 4.

title: bicycle club baked boneless chicken
directions: Slice onion and mushrooms; saute in margarine (about 1/4 cup) until tender.
Brown/saute each side of chicken.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover with onion and mushrooms.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes or until tender.
Before serving, sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese and melt.

title: 2 x 5 soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Half a batch is just as good and it's so quick.

title: wacky cake
directions: Measure out and combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix thoroughly until blended with spoon (not electric mixer); pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when touched; let cool and top with white or chocolate frosting.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly.
Add baking powder and salt to cake flour. Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: ground meat and cabbage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a greased casserole pan. Bake at 325° for about 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato soup
directions: Put all of the ingredients in a large pot and cook for one hour.
Stir occasionally.
Transfer to a soup tureen and serve hot.
Replenish as needed.
Sit back and enjoy!

title: green (english) pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, Velveeta cheese, Cheddar cheese and eggs in buttered 2 1/2 qt. casserole. Add cooked macaroni, fold in thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick jambalaya
directions: Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat.
Cook chicken in skillet 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until light brown.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Cook rice and vermicelli mix (without seasonings) in skillet over medium high heat, stirring frequently, until golden brown.
Gradually stir in water, tomatoes and seasonings from rice and vermicelli mix.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in sausage and chicken; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until liquid is absorbed and chicken is no longer pink in center.
This has 11 grams carbohydrate.

title: satu mare stuffed cabbage leaves(romania)
directions: Boil water in 3 quart pan, add cabbage leaves and salt, boil for 5 minutes.
Drain cabbage.
Preheat oven to 375F.
Mix beef, rice, onions, salt, pepper, garlic, oregano, basil and eggs, blend well.
Spoon beef mixture onto cabbage leaves, roll up cabbage leaves.
Place cabbage leaves in baking dish.
Blend tomato sauce, water, brown sugar, and cornstarch until it makes a smooth mixture. pour over cabbage rolls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 40-45 minutes, spoon sauce over cabbage rolls 2-3 times while baking.

title: green bean dip
directions: Drain and puree beans in blender.
Saute onion in butter until tender; add to beans in blender.
Add chopped mushrooms and eggs. Add walnuts.
Blend a few seconds more to mix thoroughly.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with crackers or dark bread.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add flour, butter, salt, sugar and pepper to corn.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Bake in greased dish at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and soup in casserole dish.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and light ravioli
directions: Cook ravioli according to package directions; drain well. Transfer to large bowl.

title: hazelnut brittle
directions: Oil an 11 x 17 pan. Stir sugar, vinegar and 1 cup water in a medium sized, heavy bottomed saucepan over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Cook, without stirring, until dark amber, 18 to 25 minutes. Stir in nuts. Pour mixture into pan. Let set until firm but still soft enough to cut. Unmold onto a cutting board. Working fast, use an oiled knife to cut into 6 rectangles. Store in an airtight container up to 1 week.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Pare and quarter potatoes.
Cook potatoes in water with two teaspoons salt until done.
Drain and return to pot.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup butter, cream cheese, chives, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Gradually add enough milk to make potatoes creamy and fluffy.
Cover tightly and refrigerate potatoes.
Can be stored up to one week.
To serve, spread potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: norma's never fail pie crust
directions: With fork, mix first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine, stirring with fork until all is moistened.

title: easy creamy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and layer in 13 x 9 pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and one package chipped or corned beef.
The second package is used for outside of cheese ball.

title: the best easy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and chips in saucepan over low heat.
Then mix with spoon remaining ingredeints.
Bake about 30 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Layer in flat bottom baking dish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk and pour over potatoes and onions.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In small saucepan combine sour cream and half and half and cook over medium heat until heated through (do not boil).
Stir in Cheddar cheese, scallions, parsley and pepper and continue cooking, stirring frequently, until cheese melts.
In medium mixing bowl combine potatoes and cheese mixture and mix well.
Spread margarine over bottom of 9-inch pie pan; turn potato mixture into pie pan and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
In cup or small bowl combine breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake until potato mixture is heated through, 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn oven control to broil, and broil until topping is lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Combine half and half or milk with pudding mix.
Whisk until well blended.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping, pecans, gingersnaps, pumpkin pie spice and pumpkin.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.

title: for a good disposition
directions: Do not bring to boil!

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
In Dutch oven, cover bottom with Doritos, using entire package.
Add meat.
Mix together all liquid ingredients and pour over hamburger and chips.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: jello cream cheese
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Chill remainder until thickened.
Pour into 6 molds. Arrange the apple slices in gelatin.
Chill until set but not firm. Beat cheese until smooth.
Blend in reserved gelatin.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Spoon into mold. Chill at least 4 hours.

title: wild grouse deluxe
directions: Dip pieces of grouse in mixture of egg, milk and spices, then roll in flour.
Put butter and oil in skillet and heat to frying temperature.
Brown pieces well on all sides.
Remove from skillet and place in single layer in baking dish.
Add drippings from skillet to soup and mix well.
Spoon over grouse.
Add water to bottom of dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Serves 4 to 6.
Results in a very moist and tasty bird!

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Add pretzels.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Put cheese and flour in plastic bag.
Quarter potatoes into wedges.
Moisten and place in bag. Shake to coat.
Place coated potatoes in dish.
Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Bake 1 hour at 350° turning once. Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: sour cream pecan tea ring
directions: Combine margarine, sour cream, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sour cream mixture, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add more flour to make a stiff dough.
On floured board knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; grease top. Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot pepper chicken
directions: Season and boil chicken until well done for approximately a half hour.
Remove from the pot.
Then skin and debone the cooked chicken.
Next, fry the chicken in peanut oil until lightly browned.
Set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tomato sauce) thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan, and pour the tomato sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs until fluffy.
Add bananas, flour, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes for bread, 25 minutes for muffins, at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: irresistible chicken
directions: Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place bread crumbs in large plastic Ziploc bag.
Add chicken, couple pieces at a time, and coat well.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender in order given. Turn blender to high speed and count to 10 slowly.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes on lower rack.

title: hot punch(good at christmastime)
directions: Heat and serve!
Best to make 1 day before serving.
Makes kitchen smell umm-ummy as it slowly simmers, so it can stay hot for serving.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add onions and saute until soft.
Remove onions from pan.
Add remaining butter and brown beef cubes, 1/2 at a time.
Return all meat to pan and toss with flour.
Add salt, pepper, marjoram, thyme, bouillon and 1 cup wine.
Bring mixture to boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Taste before serving.
Correct seasoning, if necessary. Ladle into serving casserole.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Place crumbs in baking dish.
Pour butter or margarine over crumbs; mix until coated.
Add salt, sugar and basil to tomatoes in saucepan and heat to boiling.
Pour over crumbs and distribute well.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes or until well browned.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl and chill.
Mix remaining ingredients and whip.
Pour on top of jelled mixture and refrigerate.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange asparagus in a 1 1/2 quart shallow pan; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over top of chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chicken salad
directions: While boiling chicken, mix mayonnaise, yogurt, Hidden Valley mix and honey.
Chill mixture for 30 minutes.
Add diced chicken and mix all ingredients.
May garnish with grape halves.

title: amaretto punch
directions: Add the 3 cans water to the orange juice.
Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: gringo chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together.
Add tomatoes, chili beans and water.
Mix and simmer for about 1 hour. Top each bowl of chili with corn chips.
Double for company.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except grated cheese and Doritos. Layer Doritos and chicken mixture in casserole dish until all used.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake(makes 6 servings)
directions: Brown pork chops.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 50 minutes longer.

title: vinegar string beans
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar.
Bring beans and oil to a boil for 10 minutes.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Simmer until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt.
Beat well; add eggs, one at a time. Stir in pecans and pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly in blender and store in refrigerator.

title: congealed peach salad
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add nuts, Cool Whip and buttermilk. Beat well.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream, margarine and sugar with pastry blender.
Add egg yolks flour, juice and rind.
Add milk and mix again.
Fold in egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: june's colossal cheeseburger
directions: In a large pan, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Stir in salt, pepper, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Simmer while preparing crust.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, water and vanilla.
Add pineapple and then mix in flour and soda.
Bake for 20 minutes in
cookie sheet pan. (It will look like it is not done.)

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Sprinkle chopped pecans over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle coconut over the nuts.
Pour cake mix (after mixed according to instructions) over coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over cake mix.
Cook in sheet cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara(to serve 4 people generously)
