directions: Cut a narrow (1-inch) X-shape all the way through beef roast with long, thin sharp knife.
Fill X-cut with sausage, ham and pimento.
Heat oil in Dutch oven until hot.
Cook beef over medium heat until brown on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer until beef is tender (about 2 hours).
Remove bay leaves. Slice beef; arrange on plate.
Skim fat from sauce.
Pour some sauce over beef.
Serve with white or Spanish rice.
Serve 8 to 10.

title: quick casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Put on bottom of dish. Crumble meat on top and top with onions.
Add salt and pepper. Mix 1/2 can water with soup and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone the chicken (save broth).
Dip the tortillas in chicken broth to soften.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the tortillas.
Put the chicken, onion, green pepper and cheese over the tortillas.
Mix the soups with the chili powder.
Do not add water to soups.
Pour over the cheese evenly. Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes until soup is bubbly.
Serve.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Blend
together shortening, salt, lemon rind and sugar. Beat in egg and milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls
on
a baking sheet.
Grease bottom of a glass.
Dip glass
in
colored sugar and flatten each cookie. Bake
to
10 minutes,
until
light golden.
Cool on rack. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Gradually stir in milk and butter.
Mix peaches, water and sugar in another bowl (use no more than 2 cups liquid).
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, melt butter. Pour batter in pan then pour fruit over batter.
During baking, batter will rise to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is well browned.

title: cucumber and potato salad
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Halve them lengthwise and scoop out seeds. Cut crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces and toss with 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Rinse well and pat dry with a towel. Refrigerate.
Cook potatoes until tender; drain well, peel and dice.
While still warm, toss in a bowl with oil, vinegar, remaining salt, pepper, onions and dill.
Cool to room temperature.
Add cukes, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Combine gently.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding mix with pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip, marshmallows, some coconut and chopped pecans.
Mix well and chill.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and put in oblong cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tarts
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk.
Fold Cool Whip into juice and milk. Fill a baked pie crust.
Let set in refrigerator at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: taco casserole
directions: Layer in order in pie dish:
spread cream cheese on bottom, place chili on top.
In separate bowl, mix together green chilies, onion and green pepper.
Spread this over top of chili.
On top, spread shredded cheese and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
About 5 minutes before taking out of oven, turn on broiler to brown cheese. Serve with taco chips.

title: oreo cookie and ice cream dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sweetened milk and ice cream in large bowl. (It is easier to mix ice cream if it has been out of freezer and in the refrigerator for a couple of hours.)
In an 11 x 13-inch pan, put layer of crumbled cookies on bottom, then ice cream mixture.
It is better to make 2 layers, ending with ice cream on top.
Save a few cookie crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Freeze and cut in squares.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Cream 4 cups powdered sugar and Crisco together well, then add remaining ingredients together and mix well.
Any leftover frosting can be frozen and still tastes great!

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: In skillet, heat oil and saute garlic and onion 4 minutes. Add zucchini and pepper.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, black beans, chickpeas, kidney beans, salt, pepper, chili powder, oregano and cinnamon; cook until heated through.
Transfer to buttered 2-quart baking pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chow chow
directions: Pour salt water over cabbage, onions, cucumbers, tomatoes and green peppers.
Let stand 2 hours and then drain.

title: cucumber-tomato salad
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise into halves.
Scoop out seeds and cut cucumbers into 1/2 inch pieces.
Mix cucumbers, tomatoes, onions and parsley.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours but no longer than 24 hours.
Mix yogurt, salt and cumin.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours and no longer than 24 hours.
Drain vegetables and fold into yogurt mixture.
Garnish with additional chopped cucumbers and tomatoes if desired.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is done.
Put cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup on top of chicken and return to oven for 15 or 20 more minutes.
Delicious to use soups for gravy on rice.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg together and press in a greased and floured pan. Mix cream cheese, *powdered sugar and 2 eggs. Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Mix potatoes, egg, onion and flour well.
Spoon out enough mixture for a 3/4-inch ball; place a 3/8-inch cube of cheese inside and work into a ball. Use extra flour to keep outside smooth.
Deep fry until golden brown; drain on paper towels and serve.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread the sausage on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the croutons evenly on top. Beat eggs, 2 cups milk and mustard together. Pour over sausage. Add 1/4 to 1/2 of the reserved milk to the soup. Pour over mix. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix together bananas, butter and eggs.
In separate bowl mix flour, sugar, cake mix and pecans. Blend the banana mixture and flour mixture together.
Bake 325° 1 hour. Cover top.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Shape in balls, about 20. Brown balls on all sides in margarine.
Mix seasoning mix with hot water; pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: hidden valley ranch quick potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes into cubes.
In a large bowl, mix potatoes, onions and dressing.
Toss gently.
Dust with paprika and garnish with bacon.
Serve warm.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In buttered 7 x 11-inch baking dish, layer half of croutons, corned beef and sauerkraut.
Top with remaining croutons and sliced Swiss cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together; pour over croutons.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Skin chicken breasts.
Blend other ingredients.
Marinate chicken overnight in this mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (or until done).

title: chicken and dumplings(quick and easy)
directions: Boil chicken, thaw tortillas.
Slice tortillas and drop into boiling broth.
Cook 20 minutes or until tender.
Add 3 tablespoons Pet cream, salt and pepper.

title: sweepstakes burnt sugar cake
directions: Make burnt sugar liquid by melting one cup of the sugar in pan on hot fire. When dark brown, add 1 cup boiling water and boil hard for 5 minutes.
Cream butter well, add sugar, then add 1/2 cup burnt sugar liquid. Beat eggs well, yolks and whites together. Add to batter and beat well.
Sift baking powder with flour and add alternately with water to the batter.
Add flavoring.
Bake in 2 layers in moderate oven.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice following instructions.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
If you freeze, do not cook prior to freezing.

title: caramel fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour 2 cups batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: pluck cake
directions: Cut biscuits into 1/4's.
Mix light brown sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, margarine and chopped nuts. Oil a Bundt or angel food pan.
Put layer of biscuit (use half of biscuits).

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and add oil into large bowl.
Pour in Starter Mix to make a firm dough.
Grease 12-inch cast-iron skillet with Crisco or equivalent.
Pinch off balls of dough English walnut size and place in skillet in warm place.
Let rise to at least twice size.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in saucepan.
Add flour, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add well beaten eggs and pecans. Pour into 2 uncooked 9-inch pie crusts and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion together.
Rinse mixture.
Add a pinch of baking powder.
Add enough flour to make a paste (like pancakes).
Fry in olive oil, turning once.
Drain.
Serve hot with sour cream or applesauce.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pan.
Heat and let simmer 20
minutes.
Pour
in
punch bowl and top with floating orange slices decorated with cloves.
Serves 20 to 25.

title: pumpkin chip cookies
directions: Mix pumpkin, egg, oil and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Add vanilla and soda/milk.
Lastly, add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: the best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, white sugar and brown sugar. Add egg.
Sift together
flour,
soda
and
cinnamon.
Add
to first mixture.
Then add
oats, walnuts or pecans and vanilla. Chill for 1 hour;
then
put
walnut-size
pieces on a greased cookie sheet. Butter the bottom
of a small glass.
Dip it in granulated sugar and
flatten
each
little
piece.
You don't need to rebutter glass
bottom;
just resugar each time.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge(radarange quickly)
directions: Blend powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl.
Then add milk and batter.
(Don't mix.)
Cook in Radarange 2 minutes.
Remove and stir just to mix ingredients.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased container and freeze for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Either ripe or green tomatoes may be used; green tomatoes just beginning to turn are very good in flavor and they are firm for slicing.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks and add the sugar. When blended, add the alcohol and set aside. Beat the whipping cream until thick and mix with the half and half. Fold this into the alcohol mixture and add the vanilla. Beat the egg whites until they peak and fold both ingredients together. Chill for 24 hours in covered container. Stir before serving. Makes 175 ounces or about 35 servings.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onions, water and salt in a large Dutch oven.
Simmer covered about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mash mixture a few times with potato masher; but leave some vegetable pieces whole.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly until soup is thoroughly reheated.

title: cherry cheese brownie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Spread into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: melon wake-up
directions: Slice cantaloupe flesh away from rind and cut into chunks. Peel and section the orange, leaving some of the pithy white area. Blend ingredients.
Serve with a spritz of lime juice.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly and top is browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients and drain.
Add tomatoes, sauce and spices.
Cook for at least one hour.
For thicker sauce, add tomato paste.

title: baked ham
directions: Wrap ham in foil.
Place in foil lined pan.
Cake in a 325° oven.
Cook 20 minutes for each pound of ham.

title: italian romaine salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine lettuce, olives, onions, cheese and anchovies. Toss lightly. Cover and refrigerate. Right before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss lightly to coat evenly. Sprinkle with dressing mix and garnish with tomatoes. DO NOT put the dressing on the salad until right before you are going to eat it. If you do, you will have mush!!!

title: oat bran muffins(heart healthy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in paper-lined muffin tins. Yields 12 servings, 107 calories and 2.6 g fat each.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 24 hours, then serve.

title: devil's food mommie cake
directions: Cook cocoa, egg yolk and 1 cup milk, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Blend in cocoa mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans, lined on bottom with waxed paper.
Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Cool and frost as desired.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken pieces in large pot.
Add diced ingredients. Add seasonings.
Pour in water and cover pot.
Bring to boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Let simmer for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken pieces; add bouillon and rice. Follow rice cooking directions.
When done, return chicken to pot to warm or debone and add to pot in bite-size pieces.
Serves 6 easily.

title: grandpa jojo's cloud nine frosting
directions: Cream together first three ingredients; then add boiling water, a little at a time (never more than half a cup).
Add a pinch of salt.
Whip at high speed until all sugar is dissolved and texture is light and fluffy.
Then add vanilla.

title: pork and ham loaf
directions: Mix crumbs, milk, slightly beaten egg and seasonings.
When milk has been absorbed by crumbs, add meat and stir only to blend. Pack into loaf pan and bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
This will make 6 servings.

title: snowballs - christmas cookies
directions: Blend ingredients and chill.
Make into balls about 1 inch in diameter and place on cookie sheet close together as they do not spread.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Yields about 48 balls.

title: zucchini bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Blend oil and sugar together.
Add vanilla, eggs and zucchini. Blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Grease two bread pans.
Pour mixture in pans.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: boiled pecans
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan.
Add pecans; return to boil for 1 minute.
Drain in a colander; rinse under very hot tap water.
Shake to remove excess water.
Place pecans in a large bowl.
Add sugar; stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Fry pecans in deep fat at 425° for 5 minutes; remove.
Drain.
Place pecans on brown paper; sprinkle with salt while hot.
Store in an airtight container.

title: spiced pickled onions
directions: In medium saucepan, combine vinegar, honey, bay leaf, mustard seed, allspice and anise seed; bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes and add onions; stir gently 2 or 3 minutes or just until onions begin to turn limp.
Remove from heat; stir in pepper and parsley. Cool; transfer to a clean pint jar.
Cover; store in the refrigerator up to 1 week.

title: smackeroon cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry.
Add sweetener, almond and vanilla extracts; beat until blended.
Fold in Rice Krispies and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon 1 inch apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: hawaiian sausage supper
directions: Combine preserves, barbecue sauce and rest of ingredients. Mix.
Simmer 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: deep dish salmon pie
directions: In a small saucepan combine soup, liquid from can of salmon and milk or cream.
Stir in salmon, potatoes, onions and seasoning.
Heat until sauce begins to simmer; stir occasionally. Empty into 2-quart casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits brown. Garnish with watercress.
Serves 4.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the soda and vinegar; set aside.
Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa in a large bowl.
Add eggs and sugar mixture to the paste.
Add sour cream and pecans.
Add buttermilk, salt, sifted flour and vanilla. Fold in vinegar and soda.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar; blend well.
Press onto bottom of spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer while preparing filling.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese and remaining sugar until smooth and light.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and cornstarch, just until blended. Stir in sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 200°, bake 45 minutes.
Turn off oven.
Cool for 3 hours or overnight.
Top with favorite topping.

title: spy wednesday biscuits(makes 40 biscuits)
directions: Place the currants in a dish; cover with hot water and set aside.
Mix the yeast with the cup of warm water in a bowl and set aside for 5 minutes until frothy.
Sift the flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender until the mixture has the texture of coarse cornmeal.
This can also be done in a food processor. Drain the currants and mix into dough.
Then, lightly stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk until ingredients are moist.
Transfer dough to a floured surface and knead gently and briefly.

title: angel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add brown sugar, white sugar and vanilla.
Combine thoroughly.
Mix together flour, cream of tarter and baking soda.
Slowly add flour mixture to other mixtures, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 8 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: You will need a frying pan, paper towels, a plate and bottle cap.

title: austrian cookies
directions: Roll in icing (powdered sugar) when partially cool after baking at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas. Cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in biscuit mix; add nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from broth.
Cool.
Cut into bite size pieces.
In large bowl, mix chicken, soup and mixed frozen vegetables.
(Do not add water to soup.)

title: german coffee cake (1)
directions: Layer cake, then fruit with syrup, a few almonds and pudding mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding mixture.
Garnish with whipped topping and pieces of fruit and almonds.
Chill several hours.
Use a large bowl or punch bowl.

title: moose balls
directions: Melt in a double boiler.
Pour over cereal mixture and form into balls.

title: cloud "9" butterscotch squares(serves 16)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
With mixer, beat margarine until creamy; add dry ingredients, pudding mix first.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
In two additions of each, add milk, alternating with milk and dry ingredients.
Begin with milk.
Mix well with each addition.
By hand, add oats and chocolate pieces.
Spread in greased 9-inch square baking pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Spread with chocolate frosting.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: beef brisket
directions: Heat oven to 275° to 300°. Liberally sprinkle both sides of brisket with garlic pepper seasoning. Place brisket in oblong turkey roaster which has been lined in foil.

Place sliced onion rings on top of brisket and wrap tightly in foil to seal. Bake at 275° to 300° for 5 to 6 hours or until knife tender. Reserve broth for dipping or to make a thin gravy to serve on the side.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in Crisco.
Mix water, egg and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture to form a ball.
Chill or freeze until ready to use.

title: bible cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Then add flour, raisins, figs and/or dates, spice and sugar.
Mix together, then blend in honey and milk.
If desired, 1/2 cup Genesis 43:11 (nuts) may be added.
Make sure all ingredients are blended thoroughly.
Place in 8-inch greased cake pan and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mock crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and make into cakes.
Brown in frying pan with as little shortening as possible.
Brown on one side, then turn to brown other side.

title: peanut butter goodies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan (ungreased).
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Chill until firm.
Cut in small squares and set on edge to dry.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Wash and hull 8 cups strawberries.
In a blender or food processor fitted with a metal blade, puree strawberries and sugar. Place strawberry mixture in a large bowl and stir in Marsala wine and lemon juice.
Stir gelatine into hot water until dissolved. Stir into strawberry mixture.
Whip 1 1/2 cups cream to medium thick.
Fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour mousse into a large glass bowl or spoon into individual dishes.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve chilled.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together 2 cups flour, butter or oleo and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: whole wheat scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease a large baking sheet.
In a large bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in raisins.
Add 1 1/3 cups milk to dry ingredients and mix lightly with fork until mixture clings together and forms a soft dough. Turn dough out onto lightly floured surface and knead gently 5 or 6 times.
Divide dough in half. With lightly floured rolling pin, roll dough into a 7-inch round. Cut into 4 wedges. Repeat with remaining half of dough.
Place scones, 1-inch apart, on a greased baking sheet.
Pierce tops with tines of fork. Brush tops with remaining milk and sprinkle with bran.
Bake scones 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 8 scones.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In mixer, cream oleo, sugar and cream cheese well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add vanilla at slower speed. Add flour a little at a time.
Pour into large greased and floured stem pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mississippi mudd cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add cocoa, eggs and vanilla and beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
While cake is warm, spread on the Marshmallow Creme.
When cool, frost.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel, slice and wash pears. As you slice them, put them in a pot of slightly salted water. This keeps them from turning dark until you finish slicing. When all of the pears are sliced, take them out of the water and rinse them. Measure 2 parts fruit and 1 part sugar into a large pot. Cook slow until sugar melts. Turn up heat so they will boil hard for 1 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally. Pears turn red when they are ready.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs; beat.
Stir in flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Add water and soda, which has been mixed together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: grape pie
directions: Slip skins from grapes - set aside.
Bring pulp to boiling point.
Press through sieve, add skins.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add lemon juice, butter and grape pulp.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle topping over pie.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 325° for 40 - 50 minutes.

title: marge's shrimp spread
directions: Grate shrimp and onion as fine as possible.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Serve with your choice of crackers.

title: red rice
directions: Fry bacon strips crisp and remove from frying pan. Saute onions and bell pepper in bacon drippings. Crumble bacon back in sauteed onions and pepper. Put this mixture and tomatoes (after mashing) in saucepan.
Add a small amount of baking soda or sugar and cook for 30 minutes. After tomatoes have boiled down, add equal amounts of rice and tomato mixture in rice steamer.
Steam until tomatoes have cooked through the rice.
Fluff rice to cook 30 more minutes. Add 1 pat of butter. Fluff with fork and serve.

title: baked pork chops with dressing
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in 1 tablespoon hot oil in a skillet.
Remove from skillet and place in baking dish.
Saute onion and celery in margarine in a small skillet. Combine with bread cubes, poultry seasoning, celery salt and 1/4 cup water; mix lightly.
Shape dressing into mounds on top of chops.
Coat potatoes with oil; place around chops.
Combine soup and 1/2 cup water; pour over chops and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed steak
directions: Break bread into small pieces.
Pour enough broth or water over to moisten. Add eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well and be sure it is moist, not dry.
Pour dressing onto the steak.
Roll the steak like a jelly roll and tie in 2 to 3 places.
Bake in electric skillet at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: sparkling citrus punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine punch, lemonade and orange juice concentrates; mix well. Just before serving, add club soda, ginger ale and ice. Float orange slices on top.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour.
Mix and heat to boiling: butter, Crisco, cocoa and Coca-Cola.
Add to sugar and flour while hot. Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, 2 beaten eggs and 1 1/2 cups miniature marshmallows.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fast fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring gently, until mixture comes to a boil; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels, stirring until chocolate melts.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Spread evenly into a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Mix together butter and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and sugar.
Place 4 portions (about a heaping teaspoonful) in a preheated waffle iron.
Cook until brown, about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll to size of buckeyes, 1-inch in diameter.
Chill.

title: ham in a can
directions: Remove key from any size canned ham and put the key where you will find it.
This is the hard part.
Using a "church key" type can opener, punch holes around the top of the can.
Make 2 holes side-by-side to make larger holes.
Place canned ham in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove can from oven and carefully pour liquid from can.
This can be used in beans or soup, if desired.
Prepare favorite sauce and pour through holes into the can to nearly fill the can.
Reduce oven to 275° and continue cooking ham for 20 minutes per pound.
Remove from oven, find the key and open can. Remove ham to platter and slice.
Serve with sauce.
Throw can away.
No pan to wash!

title: pepper belly chicken
directions: Soak corn tortillas in chicken broth. Combine in saucepan over low heat remaining ingredients. Layer tortillas in bottom of casserole dish. Pour 1/2 of mixture over tortillas, then cover with remaining tortillas. Pour rest of mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Pour half batter in pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: rice pilaff
directions: Microwave 5 minutes on High, then 15 to 20 minutes on 50% power or Medium.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Add the mushrooms; cook through, but don't let rice get mushy.
Serve hot, topped with parsley.

title: easy northern pike loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl, combine cracker crumbs and milk.
Let stand to moisten about 5 minutes.
Stir in fish, cream of shrimp soup, eggs, green onion, lemon pepper and garlic powder.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake until loaf is golden brown and knife comes out clean (55 to 60 minutes).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the corn syrup, sugar, vanilla, eggs and peanut butter; pour into the unbaked shell.
Bake in a 350° oven 50 to 55 minutes.
The center will look "wobbly" but will set as the pie cools.
When cool, cover with Dream Whip and sprinkle with chopped peanuts.

title: chicken gravy
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring constantly until brown.
Pour in chicken broth.
Stir until desired thickness.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except coconut. Roll in balls. Roll in coconut.

title: angel food cake
directions: Follow cake mix recipe.
Add the coffee.
Whip the cream for icing.
Brown shaved almonds in pan.
Sprinkle over whipped cream icing.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Wash, pare and slice potatoes. Cook with the carrots in boiling water to cover until tender. Drain. Saut bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towel and crumble. Saut onions and celery in 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat. Combine all ingredients except cheese. Simmer 30 minutes. Garnish each serving with Cheddar cheese.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan; mix all the ingredients. Add peaches last. Bake at 350° until done.

title: peppy peppers
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and cut lengthwise.
Combine rice, Velveeta cubes, celery and cilantro. Mix lightly.
Place in shallow baking dish. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa to a rolling boil, then count 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let harden or lightly greased 10 x 13-inch pan and spread in pan.
Let harden and cut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Fold into drained broccoli; add salt to taste.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly.

title: onion, ham and cheese chowder
directions: Cook cubed potatoes in boiling water until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain, reserve liquid.
Add enough water to reserved liquid to make 1 cup.
In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Add milk and potato water all at once.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add chopped ham and cheese; stir to melt cheese. Add potatoes.
Salt to taste. Serves 8.

title: jalapeno salsa
directions: Mix peppers and vinegar in blender.
Add catsup to pepper mixture in boiler and bring to a boil.
Cut heat down and simmer for 30 minutes.
Let cool and pour back into catsup bottles.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce; stir well and pour into a 9 inch square pan. Freeze until firm; cut into squares, and serve on lettuce.
Yield: 9 servings.

title: wilma's cheddar cheese salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello with boiling water.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream.
Mix well and let stand until thickened.
Add pineapple and juice and cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: kiddie chow
directions: Melt margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips in heavy pot.
When melted, pour over Chex cereal.
Stir slowly.
Put sugar in brown paper bag and pour in the Chex mixture.
Seal and shake until well coated.
Pour into a bowl and serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells for 10 minutes; drain.
Cook frozen spinach; drain well.
Mix with Ricotta, egg and cheese.
Stuff shells.
Combine sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Put 1/2 cup of sauce on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place stuffed shells on top of sauce.
Dab with sauce and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to make two cups.
Bring almost to a boil and add gelatin and marshmallows. Let dissolve.
Remove from heat and cool until slightly firm.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple and nuts and mix together.
Fold in sweetened whipped cream.
Pour in large mold and chill.

title: sharon's ice cream
directions: Vanilla:
Beat eggs in large bowl with fork.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; mix thoroughly.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine the two mixtures; roll into 2 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
Slice and bake about 5 minutes at 350°.

title: dip in loaf of french bread
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Prepare bread loaf by cutting out large circle in loaf.
Cut removed portion of bread into cubes.
Pour mixture into hollowed out place in loaf.
Dip cut cubes of bread into mixture.

title: cavatini (pizza hut)
directions: In a large skillet, brown the meats, onion and green pepper. Drain off excess fat.
Add pepperoni and Ragu sauce.
Cook on medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add noodles.
Stir well.
Turn out into a deep 9 x 13-inch greased or sprayed casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven until cheese melts.
Serve with optional garlic bread.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool, bone it and cut up into small pieces. In mixing bowl, mix soup and milk.
Add the chicken.
Arrange tortilla chips in casserole dish.
Add shredded cheese.
Add the chicken mixture.
Add another layer of tortilla chips.
Finish off with another layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Add sugar, syrup and water. Cook, stirring often, to hard candy stage (300°). Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts. Pour in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool. Spread top with half the chocolate and half the finely chopped nuts. Turn over and repeat with chocolate and nuts. Chill. Break in pieces like peanut brittle.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Chill.

title: fruit tapioca
directions: In a saucepan, combine juice and cinnamon.
Stir in tapioca and let it soak for five minutes.
Bring tapioca to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and stir.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: bacon dip
directions: Mix all together.
Mound into dish and garnish with parsley flakes.

title: tabuli salad
directions: Soak tabuli (bulgur wheat) in oil and lemon juice while cutting up the vegetables.
Mix all remaining ingredients together with the wheat mixture.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
It gets better as time goes on.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine together.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Keeps well for several days.

title: bacon bits
directions: Cut bacon strips in quarters.
Press each into cracker crumbs. Fold into a roll and anchor with toothpicks.
Let set at least 2 hours.
Place under broiler to brown.
Turn for cooking both sides.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, two tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press on bottom and up sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: olive filled cheese balls
directions: Mix butter and cheese until smooth.
Add flour, pepper and celery seed; mix to blend well, kneading dough with hands to form a ball.
Spread a scant teaspoon full of dough thinly around olive.
Place 8 to 10 balls in a round microwave dish.
Cook in microwave oven for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Repeat, cooking all cheese balls.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fudge cake
directions: Put cocoa and Crisco in a bowl.
Add boiling water; let cool. Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and Crisco with cocoa mixture very well.
Add sour cream, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in either 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake pans or 1 oblong pan.
Be sure to grease and flour pans.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds and grind peppers in food chopper or food processor. Save the juice and mix it with the vinegar and sugar. Bring to full boil on stove. Boil 5 minutes. Add ground peppers and cook 2 more minutes. Cool 5 minutes and add Certo. Bring back to full rolling boil for 1 to 2 minutes. Cool about 5 minutes. Skim and pour into sterilized glasses. Seal.

title: corned beef and emerald sauce
directions: Cook corned beef covered with water in a large pot, with onion, celery, carrots, bay leaf and rosemary for 3 hours.
Remove meat and add potatoes and cabbage for 1 hour.

title: frozen peaches and cream mousse
directions: Puree peaches in
food processor or blender.
In medium mixing bowl, combine
pureed
peaches,
sour
cream, sugar and lemon juice.
In large mixing bowl, stir ice cream, just until softened; fold in peach mixture.
Turn into the Jel-ring mold. Apply seal and
freeze
several hours or overnight until firm. If desired, fill
center
of unmolded dessert with fresh raspberries;
drizzle with
some
of
the
raspberry sauce.
Spoon remaining mixture over
and
around the dessert.
Garnish with peach slices and mint leaves; serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: joanna's salad
directions: Dissolve the jello and sugar in the hot water. Add the cold water, strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of this mixture into a dish (approximately 9 x 9-inch) and let it jell.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Knead together all ingredients.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Work with part of dough at a time so remaining dough stays cold.
Roll out dough on sugar.
Cut into squares.
Fill each square with strawberry or apricot jam.
Fold each square over jam to form a triangle.
Press edge with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy salisbury steak
directions: Mix ground chuck, egg, onion, bread crumbs and 1/4 cup mushroom soup.
Form patties and brown in skillet.
Drain fat off. Pour the rest of the mushroom soup over the patties.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In blender container, combine milk, egg and Ricotta cheese and process until smooth, scraping down sides of container as necessary; set aside.
In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add garlic and saute until softened, about 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low and add egg mixture, Parmesan (or Romano) cheese, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, 3 to 5 minutes (do not boil).
Add broccoli, cauliflower and carrot to sauce and cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables are heated through, about 1 minute.
Arrange pasta on serving platter and top with vegetable-cheese mixture.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; drain.
Combine next 11 ingredients; toss well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Spoon into lettuce lined dish.
Arrange tomato slices and egg wedges around edges.
Garnish with parsley.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips, milk and butter over low heat.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Pour into greased pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until golden.
Cut into 2-inch squares to serve as appetizers.
Good warm or cold.

title: crock pot macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. grate cheese;
mix all ingredients and put in crock pot.

title: peach skillet upside-down cake
directions: Drain peaches well.
Melt margarine and brown sugar in 10-inch heavy skillet.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and place peach slices in center, forming circle.
Scatter cherries between peaches.
Sprinkle with nut pieces.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add the 3 eggs. Bake in 9-inch glass pie plate at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before putting on topping.

title: melvena's delicious jellied old fashioned cole slaw
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water. Add the cold water and chill until just syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients (except cabbage).
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in the cabbage and pour into mold. Refrigerate until ready to serve. This should be done ahead and cannot be frozen.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be doubled.

title: quick date bread(makes two loaves)
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in a large bowl.
Stir in dates. Mix yogurt and molasses together in a separate bowl, then stir into flour mixture.
Place batter
in two lightly oiled 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch bread pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour or until browned and baked through.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: christmas sugar and spice cookies
directions: Stir together
butter, sugar and honey; do not overmix. Stir together flour, baking powder and cocoa;
stir into sugar mixture. It
will
be slightly lumpy and dry.
Beat eggs with cinnamon, cardamom and cloves; stir into first mixture.
Press the coarse dough
into an 8-inch log;
wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate 1 hour or longer.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa, add butter and stir constantly over low heat until butter is completely dissolved.
Add milk slowly. Increase heat to medium and boil 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix orange slices with 1/2 of the flour.
Add rest of the flour, baking powder, nuts, brown sugar and eggs.
Mix well. Spread on greased cookie sheet (approximately 10 x 5-inch).
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes, until just barely brown.
Frost with powdered sugar icing while still hot.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy Dutch oven.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.

title: italian casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: scratch brownies
directions: Blend melted butter or oleo, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat well with spoon. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat a 350°
oven.
Coat angel food cake pan with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: hash
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter. Add the potatoes and beef. Pour the cup of gravy over and bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350° or cook on top of stove for about 20 minutes.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of loaf pans.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter in large mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar; beat at high speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs; beat well.
At low speed add dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips and 1/2 cup walnuts.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake for 65 to 75 minutes until cake tests done. Insert toothpick in center of loaf; done when comes out clean.

title: boiling water pastry
directions: In bowl, combine shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening melts; add flour, salt and baking powder.
Chill. Makes 8-inch double crusts.

title: jimmie's pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers, place in jar.
Mix vinegar and sugar and stir until dissolved, add celery seed and pour over cucumbers. Invert jar at intervals over the next couple of days.
These do not seal and, therefore, should be frozen (can use plastic freezer boxes) or kept in refrigerator.

title: aunt minnie's relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook over real low heat.
Boil until thick, approximately 5 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Place onion and oil in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Cover; microwave for 2 to 3 minutes on High (to make onions tender).
Stir in rest of the ingredients.
Reduce temperature to Medium; cook 3 to 6 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: ooey gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, egg and powdered sugar.
Spread onto cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting into bite size squares.

title: pumpkin cake bars
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves together; pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Drizzle melted butter over mix; spread chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Then add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating well.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Pour into three 8-inch or 9-inch cake layer pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken bone side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: brisket on the grill
directions: Trim as much fat off brisket as possible.
Sprinkle liberally with salt and pepper.
Rub Cajun seasoning on both sides of beef (about 1 tablespoon per side).
Wrap in aluminum foil; seal tight, shiny side in.
Place in refrigerator at least 2 hours or overnight.
Place on grill (low heat) and cover for 2 1/2 hours, turning halfway through.

title: dijon reuben en croute
directions: In 1 tablespoon margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in kraut, 1/4 cup mustard and caraway seed.
Melt remaining margarine. Stack phyllo sheets.
Brush between each sheet with melted margarine.
Top with layers of corned beef, Swiss cheese and kraut mixture to within 1 inch of edges.
Roll from long end jelly roll fashion tucking in ends.
Brush seams with melted margarine.
Place roll seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Cut slits on top of roll 1/2 inch deep in 12 even sections for main dish or 24 for appetizers.
Serves 6 as main dish.
Use remaining ingredients for sauce:
1/4 cup mustard, sour cream and pickle relish.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Melt butter mixture gradually, mixing well.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: beef roladen
directions: Slice meat into strips.
Spread mustard on each strip.
Lay a slice of bacon on top.
Cut pickles in half lengthwise and lay one half pickle spear on bacon.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons diced onions on top.
Roll up the meat and secure with 2 to 3 toothpicks.
Brown in oil on all sides.
Put into a roasting pan and add 1 cup water. Cover and cook in a 200° oven for 4 to 6 hours.
Thicken with a little flour, if desired.
Serve with potatoes or noodles.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain corn and peas.
Dissolve sugar and spices in oil and vinegar.
Add vegetables.
Let stand overnight or longer.

title: baked apple donuts
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, nutmeg, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Combine eggs, milk and apples and add to crumb mixture.
Mix quickly until thoroughly blended.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans while warm.
Roll in melted margarine, then in mixture of 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix flour, salt and cold water in a saucepan to make a smooth paste.
Add hot water and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens and changes from white to a darker color.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring or Tempera.
(Wintergreen or vanilla flavoring may be added to reduce the flour odor).
To create interesting textures, add sand, saw dust or coffee grounds.
The finger paint is usable for 1 week.
It will mold if kept longer.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Roast meat for approximately 1 to 2 hours (depending on size). Mix together remaining ingredients and add to water already in pan after having roasted the meat.
Slice meat very thin.
Return meat to pan and cook again for approximately 45 minutes.
Serve with hard rolls.

title: sourdough french bread
directions: Pour warm water into a large bowl; stir in yeast.
Add starter, 4 cups flour, salt and sugar.
Stir vigorously about 3 minutes with a wooden spoon.
Turn into a large greased bowl; cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Mix soda with 1 cup of extra flour and stir in.
The dough will be very stiff. Turn dough out onto a floured board and begin kneading.
Add 1 cup extra flour to control the stickiness.
Knead until satiny, 5 to 8 minutes.
Shape into two oblong loaves or one large loaf.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cover and place in a warm place. Let rise until nearly double in size.
Just before baking, brush outside with water and make slashes on the top with a sharp knife. Bake at 400° until crust is a medium dark brown, about 45 minutes.

title: french toast
directions: Sift the flour, salt and baking powder and add to eggs and milk.
Dip bread and fry in 1/2 cup fat in deep skillet (1/2-inch deep) or electric frypan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix seasoning with potato flakes and cheese.
Use chicken pieces; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tender.

title: hare in herbs and wine
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and marinate rabbit in mixture 24 to 48 hours.
Remove rabbit and coat with flour.
Brown in small amount of olive oil.
Remove rabbit and place in casserole. Strain marinade, reserving vegetables.
Boil the liquid down by half.
Saute vegetables along with 1 cup onion.
Brown.
Add chicken broth.
Pour liquid and vegetables over rabbit.
Add tomatoes.
Salt lightly.
Cook about 1 hour, covered, either on top of stove or in 325° oven.

title: cantaloupe pie(serves 6)
directions: Cut cantaloupe in half; remove seeds and rind.
Cut a few thin slices of melon and reserve for garnish.
Cut remaining melon in chunks; puree in blender or processor.
(There should be 3 cups of puree.)
In a small saucepan, combine sugar and gelatin.
Stir in orange juice.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar and gelatin dissolve.
Stir in melon puree.
In blender, combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup melon puree.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Stir back into melon mixture in pan.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with melon slices and whipped cream.

title: eggplant fritters
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Boil until tender (mushy).
Drain and return to pot or mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until completely mixed.
Using teaspoon, drop into hot grease. Fry until golden brown and turn.
Makes about 20 fritters.

title: best pie crust
directions: Pour melted lard and water in bowl.
Stir in enough flour (sifted) until dough is stiff.
Knead half of dough; roll out. For 1 pie crust, half the recipe.
Place crust in pie pan.
Put in filling.
Bake.

title: brunch
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch pan.
Arrange bread on bottom.
Blend ham, cheese, milk, salt, eggs and mustard and put on top of bread. Refrigerate overnight or 3 hours.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour and measure with salt.
Cut in margarine as for pastry.
In another bowl, combine molasses and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Dissolve soda in hot water and add.
Combine flour and molasses and beat until well blended.
Chill.
Turn out on lightly floured board and roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in circles and place on greased baking sheet, 1-inch apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until a deep rich brown.

title: french barbecue chicken
directions: Batter and fry chicken until brown or purchase already fried. Combine next 4 ingredients in sufficient multiples to cover desired amount of fried chicken.
Place fried chicken in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Cover with sauce.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
Another hour is okay.
The chicken may fall off the bones when serving.

title: frozen fruit salad(from the kitchen of carolyn norman)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into paper-lined muffin pan for individual servings, or pour into Pyrex dish.
Freeze.
Serves 24.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cut broccoli, cauliflower and onions into small pieces.
Mix dressing by directions on package.
Pour dressing over vegetables and stir.

title: almond coconut crunch
directions: Combine almonds and coconut; spread in thin layers over bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, melt butter or margarine, then blend in remaining ingredients.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture reaches soft-crack stage (290°).
Remove from heat and pour in thin stream evenly over almonds and coconut. Cool, then break into pieces.
Store in airtight container. Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: baked lobster tails
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
With sharp knife, split each lobster tail down center, but not all the way through.
Arrange lobster tails in baking dish.

title: avocado with tahini
directions: Peel and mash avocado thoroughly.
Blend together crushed garlic, lemon juice, salt and tahini.
Mix with avocado.
Serve as a dip with crackers.

title: pork chop and pasta dinner
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Place macaroni in 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
In skillet, brown chops in hot cooking oil; drain off excess fat.
Season with a little salt and pepper.
Arrange chops over macaroni in baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, onion, Worcestershire sauce, basil, sugar, salt, garlic powder, oregano and pepper; pour over chops and macaroni. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Beat
together
sugar, butter and egg whites.
Then mix in milk, flour and baking powder.
Fold in hickory nuts.
Bake in
2 round cake pans (10-inch) at 350° until sponge back when touched with
finger.
Use
suggested hickory nut icing, then sprinkle with nuts.

title: broccoli, rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
In separate pan saute 1 onion in butter or oleo.
When done, mix chicken soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add rice and broccoli.
Put into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: arnold's melba thin bread
directions: Trim off crusts, 1/2 each slice.
Spread with thin layer of Cheez Whiz and sprinkle with seeds.
Bake in slow oven until crisp.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/4 cup sugar until stiff.
Beat egg yolks with 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix whites and yolks.
Add cream, milk, whiskey and rum.
Serve chilled with grated nutmeg.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; season lightly with salt and pepper.
Add carrot, onion, pimento and soup.
Pour melted margarine over stuffing and mix well.
Add 1/2 stuffing mix to squash and place in buttered casserole.
Cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald the milk and pour it over the bread which has been cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Beat the eggs slightly.
Add the sugar, salt and vanilla to them.
Put into a buttered baking dish and add the milk and bread cubes. Add the melted butter and stir to mix well. Place the dish in a shallow pan of boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mound bars
directions: Mix and spread on crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost with 1 package melted chocolate chips.

title: jumbo oatmeal peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: craig's favorite chicken
directions: Prepare sauce mix and leave on back of stove.
Dip breasts lightly in flour with salt and pepper to taste and brown on both sides in frying pan using 1/4-inch of olive oil.
Do not cook chicken through, just lightly brown 1 minute each side.
Leave oil in pan.

title: very easy mayo rolls
directions: Mix all together and bake in muffin pan (spray with non-stick cooking spray) at 425 for 10-15 minutes until golden brown. Butter and Serve!

title: orange smoothee
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or a jar.
Cover and blend or shake until frothy and smooth.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salt water until tender; drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper. Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle Durkee onions on top.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes at 350° or until heated through.

title: corn bread pie
directions: Brown hamburger; add tomato soup, water, corn, onion and chili powder.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix corn bread mix and pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until corn bread is brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin.
Sprinkle with salt (about 1/2 teaspoon per cucumber).
Let stand in refrigerator for 1 1/2 hours.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, chives, salt, vinegar and paprika. Whip until light.
Add to the cucumbers and let stand until ready to serve.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter slightly in heavy 10-inch skillet.
Spread with brown sugar and layer of pineapple rings.
Blend remaining ingredients well.
Fold in 3 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour over mixture in skillet and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Turn upside down on cake platter.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix together flour and margarine. Spread in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cream together sugar and cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on top of baked crust. Top with cherries.

title: cider treat
directions: Cook slowly
for
20 minutes. Strain. Serve hot with lemon slices.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add, alternating with milk, to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 4 greased and floured pans, 8 or 9-inch round or square.
Bake at 325° until cake tests done, about 30 minutes.
Add few drops of red food coloring to one layer and cocoa to another layer to make different colored layers.
Ice cake.

title: ranch beans
directions: Mix together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Freezes nicely.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease round cake pan or 2 loaf pans. Sift dry ingredients; add raisins.
Set aside.

title: surprise oreo tunnel cake
directions: Prepare angel food cake according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Place cake on serving plate.
Slice 1-inch layer from top and set aside.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes and coat with salt, pepper and flour. Brown the meat in shortening. Add all the rest of the ingredients in a large pot.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Scatter bacon and cheese over bottom of crust.
Prepare basic custard; beat until blended the eggs, milk, cream, butter, flour, salt, cayenne pepper and nutmeg.
Pour custard over bacon and cheese.
Bake in preheated 375° oven, about 40 minutes or until custard is firm and puffy and lightly browned.
Serve warm or let it cool.

title: cream cheese chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the cream cheese, milk and salts in a blender; blend until well mixed.
Butter a 3-quart casserole dish and place broccoli on bottom.
Pour half of cheese mixture over broccoli.
Place chicken on top; pour rest of cheese mixture over chicken.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Place onion rings on top during last 5 minutes of cooking.
Makes 8 servings.

title: foolproof microwave fudge
directions: Melt morsels and milk on low in microwave, stirring constantly.
Add in nuts, if desired.
Spread evenly into a non stick 8 inch square pan.
Cool for 2 hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup of oil until crumbly, reserving 1 cup for later use.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13x9x2 pan.
Bake 15 mins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corns, sour cream, oil, eggs and sugar.
Then add cornbread mix.
Blend well.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Mix Eagle Brand, lemonade and Cool Whip.
Slice the two layers (make 4 layers).
Put filling in between and on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour or more.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and margarine and add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add Raisin Bran.
Mix with first ingredients.
Bake as desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Batter keeps up to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes (early in the day) in their jackets.
Cool; peel; dice.
Put in nonstick pan or frypan; add light cream and Swiss cheese in pieces and heat on stove until cheese melts; mix throughly.
Put in buttered 2-quart casserole; let set 2 hours. Sprinkle on buttered Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake in oven 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: filet mignon with mushroom and onion gravy
directions: Rub Filet Mignon with thyme, pepper and 1 teaspoon of salt. Over medium high heat in a 10-inch skillet, heat 1 tablespoon of oil.
Cook steaks 5 minutes on each side or until desired doneness.
Remove to a plate and keep warm.

title: no-peek beef
directions: Sprinkle meat in a casserole dish with onion soup mix.
Cover with mushroom soup which has been diluted with 1 can of water. Add mushrooms.
Cover with a tight fitting lid and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Top with remaining lettuce.

title: brisket of corned beef
directions: Soak brisket for 1 hour in cold water.
Remove and pat dry. Place on large piece of aluminum foil; reinforce center where you place the brisket.
Now, cover with orange, onion and carrots. Last, add good amount of pickling spices.
Seal foil and place on pan.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Place all platter (brisket sliced). Enjoy with favorite potatoes, etc.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Cook sausage until nearly done.
Add onion and celery.
Cook slowly 10 minutes.
Add hamburger and seasoning; brown.
Add bread crumbs until the fat from the meat has been absorbed.
Let cool before stuffing the turkey and keep it from becoming dry.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in skillet.
Cook until light brown. Gradually add broth and milk; stir until smooth and thick.
Stir in chicken, Veg-All, salt and pepper.
Place 1 pie crust in dish. Pour chicken mixture in; top with other crust.
Cut 2 to 3 holes in top; bake until brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Then roll biscuit quarters in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place 1/2 biscuit quarters in Bundt pan and sprinkle with 1/2 pecans.
Melt butter and add brown sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture over biscuits, then layer remaining biscuits and pecans and top with rest of butter, brown sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted margarine and pat into 13 x 9 x 2 1/4-inch pan.
Whip together powdered sugar, soft margarine and eggs until smooth and fluffy; spread over crumb mixture.
Layer pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top and decorate with cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: mean pork and beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, not covered.

title: brazilian brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a bowl, whip the nonfat dry milk and ice water until stiff peaks form.
In another bowl, beat the eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Add brown Sugar Twin, melted margarine, instant coffee powder and vanilla.
Sift together the remaining ingredients; stir flour mixture into egg mixture.
Add mashed bananas; fold whipped dry milk into batter.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until tests done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil 1 chicken and debone.
Boil spaghetti in broth according to package directions.
Drain and add to chicken.
In microwave in large bowl, cook celery and onion in oleo until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add soups and tomatoes.
Cook until hot and bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Add cubed Velveeta.
Cook 1 more minute to melt. Stir into chicken and spaghetti.

title: homing grits bread
directions: In a saucepan, bring 6 cups of water to a full boil.
Stir in grits and salt and cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Remove from stove and add oleo, cheese, Tabasco and eggs.
Pour into well-greased small pan and bake 1 hour or until golden brown.
Cool.
Slice as bread or serve topped with creamed chicken or tuna.

title: water chestnuts with bacon
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts and secure with a toothpick.

title: meat bundles(can freeze)
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion and seasoning.
Divide meat into 6 portions.
On wax paper, shape into patties.

title: ost kaker(swedish cheesecake)
directions: Combine eggs (well beaten) with creamed cottage cheese and sugar.
Mix flour with milk until smooth.
Fold into egg, cottage cheese and sugar mixture.
Add almond extract (I usually add more extract for flavor).
Pour into greased baking dish.
(I use a 3-quart Corning Ware.)
Place in pan of hot water to bake at 400° about 1 hour.

title: raisin crumb pie
directions: In a saucepan, add cold water, 1 1/2 cups sugar and the raisins.
Cook until raisins are plump and tender.
Set aside to cool.
Mix the flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup of the mixture and set aside for top.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 1 side of bread slice.
Place buttered side down in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of sausage and 1 cup of cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour half over cheese layer.
Repeat layering with bread buttered side up.
Cover with foil; chill for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: sticks and stones
directions: Mix butter, curry powder, Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and
garlic
salt.	Add remaining ingredients and stir. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mary lynn's beer biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°; reduce temperature to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: savory london broil
directions: Rinse London broil in water; pat dry.
Place London broil in skillet with oil.
Brown very well on both sides, over medium heat.
Transfer beef to a crock-pot.

title: oven baked pecan-crusted chicken fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Lightly grease a barge baking sheet.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine and simmer 1 1/2 hours, then add cheese.
Simmer gently.
Do not boil.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: southern corn cakes
directions: Mix egg, buttermilk and shortening in a small bowl.
Stir into mixture of soda, sugar, baking powder, salt, cornmeal and flour in bowl; mix well.
Bake on hot, greased griddle until golden brown on both sides.

title: cut-out cookies
directions: Mix all together; roll out.
Cut in any shape and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: banana bread(diabetic)
directions: Allow margarine to come to room temperature so that it is soft.
Cream margarine and 1/2 cup flour, mixed with the salt, soda and fructose.
Add the beaten eggs; mix well.
Add remaining flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add the vanilla and mashed bananas.
Put dough in a standard size metal loaf pan which has been greased with part of the margarine (I always use what is left on the wrapper).
Shake a little flour around in the pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes, or until it is hot.
Makes 18 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll in cinnamon and white sugar. Put in greased Bundt pan.
If using nuts, put them in first.
Melt oleo, brown sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: rock cakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and sugar in a bowl.
Cut the butter into small pieces and rub it in until the mixture resembles coarse breadcrumbs.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 2 hours.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda and milk alternating each.
Cut up dates and candy.
Add fruit, coconut and nuts to batter.
Bake in a tube pan at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
(Roll fruits in some extra flour before adding to cake.)

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix well and bring to a boil the margarine, water and cocoa. Add to flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Add eggs, soda (just a pinch if using self-rising flour), buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 45 minutes (or until toothpick comes out clean) at 350°.

title: tempt-me-truffles
directions: Gradually add 4 cups powdered sugar to cream cheese, mixing well after each addition.
Add chocolate and vanilla; mix well. Chill several hours.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in almonds, cocoa or addition powdered sugar.
Chill.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookie.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain and mash.
While potatoes are still hot, add salt, cinnamon, butter and syrup.
Blend well. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish; top with marshmallows.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Season to your taste.

title: green bean dish
directions: Drain green beans; place in baking dish.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and small can of mushrooms.
Heat through.
Top with cheese and almonds; return to oven to melt cheese.

title: microwave potato, tomato and onion casserole
directions: Cook onion, garlic, thyme and 1 tablespoon oil in a 2-quart shallow dish, covered, on High for 6 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.
Meanwhile, peel potatoes and slice.
Stir potatoes, tomatoes, pepper and salt into onions.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Coat a 5-cup decorative mold with nonstick cooking spray.
In a medium saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup orange juice. Let stand 1 minute. Cook over low heat for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring often, until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups
orange juice and cranberry sauce until well combined. Pour into prepared mold and chill 24 hours until firm. With tip of sharp knife, carefully release gelatin from mold.
Dip mold into warm water to the depth of the gelatin contents for 5 seconds. Tilt or shake gently to loosen.
Invert with serving dish on top. Shake to release.

title: party peas
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in Pyrex dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 48 hour slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion and bell pepper.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Mix chicken, grapes and cashews together.
Blend together the mayonnaise, yogurt, honey and pepper. Combine the chicken mixture with the dressing.

title: finger steak
directions: Unroll flank steak.
Cut in half lengthwise, then angle cut strips 1/4 to 1/2-inch wide.
Whip together egg, ginger, garlic and soy sauce.
Marinate strips 15 minutes or longer.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Use a large heavy skillet.
Wash, peel and cut eggplant (1/4-inch slices).
Dip slices in egg, salt and pepper.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Melt shortening in skillet at medium heat. Add eggplant slices and lay flat.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn several times until crisp and brown.
Add more shortening if necessary.
Serves 6.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: In 10-inch skillet, over medium heat, brown chops.
Stir in sauce.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: custard amaretto cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, sift together cake mix and cornstarch. Add water, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour pans.
Pour half the batter (3 cups) into 1 pan.
Add cocoa to remaining batter, stirring until blended.
Pour this batter into other pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove and cool on rack.
Freeze layers for 2 hours.
Split each layer in half.
Brush each layer with Amaretto.
Put a chocolate layer on plate and spread with 1/3 custard filling.
Repeat with remaining layers ending with yellow.
Frost with whipped cream.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Remove meat from bones and cube in 2-inch squares.
Saute chicken cubes in 3 tablespoons butter until lightly browned and cooked through. Remove chicken from pan. Deglaze pan with vermouth.
Mix cornstarch, broth and tarragon. Add to pan drippings.
Cook, stirring, until thickened and clear.
Add lemon, remaining butter, garlic powder, dash of salt, white and black pepper.
Return chicken to pan and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: church salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix crackers, 1/2 sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites to a stiff peak; add remaining sugar.
Fold mixture into egg whites. Pour into buttered pie plate and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool; top with whipped cream.
One half day before serving, sprinkle top with grated semi-sweet or bitter chocolate.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and drain off grease.
Put all ingredients into crock-pot and put on high to melt cheese.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with nacho chips.
Recipe may be cut in half.

title: marshmallow roll
directions: Melt at low heat the butter and milk chocolate.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, sugar and egg.

title: quick french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in saucepan until golden.
Stir in flour.
Add bouillon cubes, water and Worcestershire sauce to onions.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Float a Melba toast round topped with 1 tablespoon cheese for each serving, or serve in individual bowls each one topped with a Melba toast and cheese.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: iowa freezer corn
directions: Drain a can of chickpeas.
Add salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover with water and a bit of olive oil.
Simmer with cover until most of liquid is gone.
Serve hot or are great cold on a salad.

title: cream soda punch
directions: Mix sugar and 2 cups water in large saucepan.
Cook on medium until sugar dissolves.
Allow syrup to cool.
Dissolve ascorbic acid in 1/2 cup water; add to sugar syrup along with lemon juice and extracts.
Cool.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, mix 1 cup syrup mixture with 2 quarts ginger ale. Add crushed ice.
Yields 90 (4 oz.) servings.
You can freeze leftover syrup.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Salt and pepper beef roast; put in large roaster.
Pour sauce over roast and put a foil tent over it.
Bake at 325° for 4 to 6 hours.
After a few hours, turn roast around.
Spoon grease off top of juice.
After 5 to 5 1/2 hours, take two forks and pull meat apart.
Serve on buns.

title: old world sauerkraut supper
directions: Place in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: heavenly ham sandwiches
directions: Slice rolls in half. Put bottom half in pan and layer ham and cheese on top. Melt butter and add all other ingredients. Drizzle over rolls. Cover with foil and refrigerate over night. The next day remove from foil and bake at 350 degrees for 10-12 minutes. Be sure all the sauce has baked into the rolls before taking out of oven.

title: martha's cabbage roll
directions: Add all ingredients, except tomato juice and cabbage, to the meat.
Wilt the cabbage leaves in hot water.
Place the meat mixture in the cabbage leaves, fasten with a toothpick and put in a baking pan.
Pour tomato juice over stuffed cabbage.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to two hours.

title: russian cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425. Combine all ingredients except eggs and buttermilk. Add eggs and buttermilk, stir. Pour batter into iron skillet or skillet with oven proof handle. Bake 45-50 minutes. Makes 10 slices.

title: flour tortillas
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in lard until particles are fine.
Add water gradually.
Form into a ball (1 inch round) and knead 5 minutes.
Cover with towel and let rest 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 10 minutes in salted water; drain.
Combine oleo, soup, mushrooms and water chestnuts in a saucepan.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Place broccoli in a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli.
Top with onion rings and grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese souffle
