directions: In double boiler, melt butter and flour.
Blend in milk.
Add beaten egg yolks and cut up cheese.
When well creamed, thickened and blended, add well beaten egg whites.
Cover and cook 7 minutes.
Never fails.
Stays fluffy even for second helpings.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. In medium bowl, combine sour cream, green onions, salt, pepper, soup and pimiento; mix well.
In prepared baking dish, layer half of potatoes, sauce and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; continue baking 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: supper on bread(easy, quick)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cut bread lengthwise.
Butter and brown bread under broiler.
Remove, then spread mixture onto bread.
Broil 10 to 12 minutes, until done.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan and add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.

title: easy chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first
five
ingredients well.
Add chocolate chips last. Spray Bundt
cake
pan
or
tube
pan with Baker's Joy. Pour cake batter in pan.
Bake
in
oven for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn out on cake rack to cool.
Needs no icing.
Moist and delicious.

title: quick whipping cream biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour with a pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Add whipping cream, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll or pat dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 13 to 15 minutes. Brush biscuits with 1/4 cup melted butter.

title: strawberry colada
directions: *You want more potent?
Use 151 proof Ron Rico rum.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings.
Roll chicken in mixture; place in bowl.
Pour remaining mixture over. Refrigerate (overnight if wanted).
Roll in bread crumbs (taking up as much sour cream as possible).
Put in a baking dish.
Melt butter and margarine.
Pour 1/2 over chicken; bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour remaining butter over.
Bake 15 more minutes.

title: venison chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion;
add chili mix and tomato juice. Simmer slowly about 2 to 3 hours.
Add a can of pinto beans the last hour.

title: pumpkin bread(fat and cholesterol free)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl and mix well.
Combine wet ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients with wet ingredients until just mixed.
Spray two loaf pans, 8 x 4-inch and divide mixture between pans.
Bake at 350° in metal baking pan or 325° in glass pan for about 50 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan and remove to rack.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Place first four ingredients in casserole dish
x 13 1/2) in order.
Mix milk and Bisquick together. Pour over top. Bake at 350 for 1 hour.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and almond extract. Gradually bear in dry ingredients.
Tint dough with food coloring. Cut with favorite cookie cutters or make balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375°.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in a deep baking dish. Sprinkle sugar and lemon juice. Sift dry ingredients together, then add beaten egg. Mix with fork until crumbly. Sprinkle evenly over peaches. Pour the melted butter or margarine over the crumb mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes or until crusty and brown.

title: sunshine angel food cake
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks.
Reserve half of egg yolks. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until stiff peaks are formed.
Beat reserved egg yolks and add to the egg white mixture. Sift cake flour and sugar 3 times.
Fold flour/sugar mixture into egg whites by hand alternately with 1 cup of sugar.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
To use, add 2 tablespoons of mix to 34 cup of hot milk.
Yields 1 1/2 cups dry mix.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Cook
onion
in
oil.
Remove onion and cook meat until lightly
brown.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broiled flounder with mustard
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Arrange the fillets on a baking sheet and sprinkle them with pepper, then brush them with the oil.
Spread the mustard evenly over the fish.
Put the fillets into the broiler, about 3-inches from the heat source.
Broil for about 2 minutes, or until golden brown.
Do not overcook.
Place on individual dishes, sprinkled with chives and wedge of lime.
Serves 4.

title: cheese cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan. Dust with graham cracker crumbs.
Sieve cottage cheese into a large mixing bowl. Add cream cheese.

Beat with high speed of electric mixer until well blended and creamy. Beating at high speed, blend in sugar, then eggs. Reduce speed to low. Add cornstarch, lemon juice and vanilla. Beat until blended.
Add melted butter and sour cream. Blend with low speed.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 325° (slow oven) about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until firm around edges.
Turn off oven; let cake stand in oven 2 hours. Remove and cool on wire rack. Remove sides of pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box. Sprinkle coconut on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle pecans on top of coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine and vanilla. Spoon over top of cake mix, coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cake will crack after baking.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Combine undrained peaches, brown sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg in saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Combine water and cornstarch; stir into peach mixture.
Cook and stir until bubbly; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Serve warm with cooked pork or poultry.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix and shape ingredients into balls, then brown on all sides in a large skillet.
Place meatballs in foil lined pan and pour the following sauce over them.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until done.
Pour off excess drippings (about 1/2).
Arrange alternate layers of rice and sausage in greased quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle each layer with chopped onion and salt and pepper.
Pour tomato soup over mixture and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: angel pudding
directions: Melt marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Whip cream.
Add pineapple, drained, then melted marshmallows.
Roll 8 graham crackers.
Place in dish.
Add cream mixture, then cover with 8 more rolled graham crackers.
Set in refrigerator to chill.
This recipe may be doubled.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry or cherry Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water. Heat cranberry sauce and add pineapple and sauce to Jell-O.
Mix well and let set in a flat dish, 9 x 13-inches.
Spread sour cream over mixture and let set 1 hour in refrigerator.
Dissolve the raspberry Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Pour over top of the other Jell-O mixture. Chill and serve.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: In a 6-inch skillet cook sausage 6 to 8 minutes over moderate heat, breaking it up with a spoon until meat is no longer pink and most of the fat has cooked out.
Drain in a strainer.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer
ingredients in this order.
Chill and serve with tortilla chips.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients, then add to first mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Top with sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Great to store in freezer also.

title: 24 hour cauliflower salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in container.
Cover and let set overnight.
Mix together 5 minutes before serving.

title: california vegetable salad
directions: Cook green beans and artichoke hearts according to package directions.
Drain; cool.
Place in salad bowl with mushrooms, olives and onions.
Combine garlic, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper. Beat well.
Pour over salad.
Toss gently to cover vegetables. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: nuts about you
directions: In a blender, blend water, orange juice and punch with bananas, honey and pine nuts on medium speed for 1 minute.
Add nut butter; mix for another minute.
Makes 5 cups.

title: mint pies
directions: You will need 18 cupcake papers.

title: turtle shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut shells into 8 pie shaped wedges. Bake on ungreased baking sheets for 7 to 9 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove shells and place on waxed paper.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel and wash onions.
Quarter the onions without cutting all the way through.
Put generous amount of margarine into split. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until tender.
(Cover with foil to prevent dark ends on onions.)
Can be cooked in microwave.

title: tuna dip
directions: Put in blender and stir.
Make a day ahead.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine ingredients and put in an 8-inch square cake pan.
Put in freezer.
When almost frozen, put in a chilled mixing bowl and beat until fluffy.
Return to cake pan, freeze until set.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Spread apricot preserves and dry onion soup over chicken breasts in a baking dish.
Mix together pineapple, water chestnuts and maraschino cherries.
Pour over the top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine milk, sugar, rice, butter, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Bake, uncovered, stirring often, for 2 1/2 hours or until rice is done. Add raisins after first hour of cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pudim
directions: Melt 1/2 cup of sugar in a tube pan directly over heat.
Turn to coat all sides of the pan.
Mix well all of the ingredients.
A blender is handy for this step.
Pour into the tube pan.
Place in a pan with about 1-inch of water.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from the oven and leave the tube pan in the pan of water until it cools.
Remove from the pan and refrigerate before serving.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Saute beef in large skillet, using 1 tablespoon butter, until brown.
Stir in tomato sauce and remove from heat.
Set aside.
Combine in a bowl the cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, scallion and green pepper. Using a 3-quart casserole, spread half of the noodles, then cover with the cheese mixture.
Add rest of noodles.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over top of noodles.
Cover with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Combine with other ingredients and mix well.
Makes 5 gallons.

title: party mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Mash while hot.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Cover and store in refrigerator (up to 2 weeks).
On party day, remove casserole from refrigerator 1 hour before baking time.
If desired, fluff up potatoes with a little milk.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: hershey delight
directions: Mix 1 cup of milk with pudding. Put in refrigerator for 10 minutes. Take out and stir Cool Whip, sour cream and Eagle Brand milk.
Layer, starting with wafers, bananas, pudding, syrup and nuts until mixture runs out.
Garnish with nuts.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat applesauce into batter.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Mix together and simmer 30 minutes. Enough for 50 hot dogs.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Chill and serve.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in deep fry.
Cook until brown.
Drain.

title: mabel dodge kerr's dumplings
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg; add milk and melted butter.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Drop from tablespoon into hot chicken stock.
Cover and cook 15 minutes without lifting lid.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into creamed mixture; blend
well.
Add	chocolate
and	nuts.
Drop
from teaspoon
2 inches
apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.	Remove from sheet immediately.	Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well in order given.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may add chopped nuts to the mixture, if desired.

title: rice balls
directions: Place in a large pot butter and onion.
Let saute.
Add 2 quarts of water; bring to boil.
Add rice; let rice cook until tender.
Add egg whites, pepper, salt and cheese; mix well. Remove from heat.
Let cool for 1 hour.
When cool, shape into balls and dip into egg yolks and bread crumbs.
(Could be stuffed with meat or cheese.)
Deep fry balls until brown.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix Cool Whip and dry pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time.

title: swiss corn
directions: Heat and drain corn.
In mixing bowl lightly beat eggs.
Add milk, onion, salt, pepper and most of the cheese.
Stir well and add corn.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cube margarine or butter over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs on top, then remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: campbell's chicken and stuffing skillet
directions: Heat butter in skillet and add chicken, cook 12 to 15 minutes or until done.
Remove chicken.
Prepare stuffing in skillet according to package directions, let stand 2 minutes.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese, cover and heat throughout.

title: dressing with cornbread
directions: *If I run short of broth, I finish by using milk.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Saute chicken and onion in oil until chicken is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add broth, vegetables and soy sauce. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork before serving. Recipe may be doubled or halved.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Mix together rice, corn, cheese and sugar.
Cook green pepper, celery, onion and jalapeno pepper in margarine until tender.
Add cooked mixture to first mixture and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Cream the shortening or butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture. Stir in peanut butter chips and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly. Remove to wire rack and cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: hot baked clam dip
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and garlic.
Add clams with juice and lemon juice; bring to boil.
Add bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, wine and Tabasco.
Place in pie dish or in casserole dish. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese (if you need more, it's okay). Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot with bagel chips, flatbreads or Town House crackers.

title: crusty garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine oil, garlic powder and paprika.
Add chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cut bread crosswise in pieces.
Brush cut sides with mixture.
Place fork in foil bag or foil paper.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until heated, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with Tostito chips.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches, or square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef and onion are brown; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spoon into pie plate.

title: little cheesecake cookies
directions: Beat all ingredients together except vanilla wafers.
Mixture will be thin.
Put wafer upside down in small muffin pans (line with small cupcake liners).
Add 1 tablespoon of mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until toothpick comes out dry.
Cook.
Top with any flavor of pie filling.

title: baked rice custard
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a boil.
Add a pinch of salt.
Add 1/2 cup converted rice.
Cover and cook on low for 20 minutes or until water is absorbed.

title: clinton's chips
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheets.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda on waxed paper.
Beat together shortening, sugars and vanilla in large bowl with electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs, beating until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture and rolled oats.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop batter by well rounded measuring teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.
Cool cookies on sheets on wire rack 2 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: county line fire department chili(approximately 15 gallon pot)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Then combine remaining ingredients. Cook for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Melt together butter and cocoa.
Add to flour and stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered baking pan.
Over the top, scatter without mixing the brown sugar, sugar and cocoa. Pour over the top the cold water or coffee.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: steamed veggies
directions: Bring water to boil in wok or vegetable steamer.
Use retainer ring or colander to keep veggies above water.
Let steam for approximately 20 minutes, or until carrots are done.
Remove.
Add salt and melted cheese, if desired.

title: corn chili
directions: Remove frozen corn from freezer to defrost while preparing other ingredients.
Brown onion, green pepper and ground beef in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and bring to boiling.
Add frozen corn and mix well until kernels are well separated.
Cover and cook until corn is done, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove bay leaf to serve.
The recipe serves six.
Add more chili powder if a hotter flavor is desired.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all ingredients together for about 30 seconds.
Makes 3 cups.

title: spaghetti pizza deluxe
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti.
Blend milk and egg; add to spaghetti.
Toss to coat.
Spray jelly roll pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread spaghetti in a pan.
Cook hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add sauce and seasoning.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Spoon over spaghetti.
Top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: one-step lasagna
directions: Combine water with sauce and ground beef. Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 1/2 cups sauce mixture. Arrange a layer of uncooked noodles over sauce. Spread half the Ricotta and half the Mozzarella over noodles.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan. Repeat with another layer of noodles, the Ricotta, Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan. Top with the remaining noodles.
Pour remaining sauce over all to cover.
Sprinkle on Parmesan. Cover with heavy-duty foil. Set on a jelly roll pan (important).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: In large pan, add margarine, water, peanut butter and cooking oil.
Bring to boil and turn off heat.
Add sugar, flour, milk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Crumb together and keep in glass container.
Do not keep in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 8 months.

title: blueberry chantilly tarts
directions: Mix together cornstarch and sugar in a medium saucepan; stir in water, lemon juice and 1 cup blueberries.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in 1 cup blueberries.
Reserve a little whipped cream.
Fold in remainder of whipped cream into blueberry mixture. Spoon into tart shells.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with remaining blueberries and whipped cream.
Yields 8 tarts.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: In a medium size baking dish, mix well the honey, mustard and soy sauce until smooth.
Place the chicken breasts in the mixture, making sure most of the chicken is well covered by it.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve and spoon mixture over chicken.

title: cornflake and nut meringues
directions: Beat egg whites in a large bowl.
Beat in sugar gradually. Beat in salt and vanilla.
Fold in nuts and cornflakes.
Push with teaspoons onto cookie sheet lined with brown paper.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes until surface is dry, but not brown.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: quick spicy chile
directions: Saute meat and minced
garlic
in a nonstick frying pan sprayed with nonfat cooking
spray.
Saute	until
all
of the pink disappears, then
add	remaining
ingredients	and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.	Contains 1.03 grams of fat per serving.

title: chicken and broccoli surprise
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Top with cheese.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: A little more sugar may be needed.

title: apple crisp
directions: In large saucepan, combine rhubarb, sugar, lemon juice and orange peel.
Over high heat, bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-high and cook 10 minutes until mixture is reduced by 1/3, stirring often.
(Rhubarb mixture should measure 1 cup.)
Chill 15 minutes until completely cooled.
In large mixing bowl with mixer, whip cream to soft peaks.
Fold in cooled rhubarb mixture and spoon into serving glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: sydney hart's tomato soup
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and simmer.
Use 3 teaspoons flour and butter to make a sauce and add to ingredients.

title: chinese 24 hour vegetable salad(make 24 hours ahead)
directions: Mix white vinegar, wine vinegar, sugar, Wesson oil, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Mix real good and put in icebox for 24 hours.
Good with vegetables, meat or sandwiches.
This recipe makes a lot and will keep a long time.
This is good to take to a church dinner.

title: hazel's peanut butter snacks
directions: Blend corn syrup and sugar together.
Bring to a boil over medium flame.
Stir in peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper or buttered cookie sheet.
Let set.

title: chocolate cringle cookies
directions: Mix oil, chocolate and sugar.
Blend in 1 egg at a time until well mixed.
Add vanilla.
Stir in salt, flour and baking powder. Chill dough 2 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop a teaspoon of dough into powdered sugar; roll into a ball.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 50 cookies.

title: anise christmas cookies
directions: Mix ingredients with flour until dry enough to roll out on a floured surface without sticking to rolling pin.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until pale gold.
Decorate with colored sugar or small candies, warm milk-confectioners sugar mix.
Put in tightly covered container; cover with wax paper and on top of that lay a piece of lettuce or apple slice on top.
This will soften cookies.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together, except Marshmallow Creme, and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
While still hot spread with Marshmallow Creme.
Cool.
Then frost with icing.

title: shrimp a la creole
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in large skillet.
Add all other ingredients, stirring after each addition.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Save out 1/2 cup.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour milk evenly over crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together sausage and biscuit mix.
Add cheese.
Mix well. Make into walnut size balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet or cookie pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanutty hot fudge cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together crumbs, margarine, and granulated sugar in small bowl, press onto bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of 9-inch springform pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar, and peanut butter in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping, pour into crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts. Chill until firm. Drizzle topping over cheesecake just before serving. 10 to 12 servings.
Prep time:
15 minutes, plus chilling

title: no knead yeast bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix other ingredients well.
Add yeast mixture and stir until a sticky blob.
Set aside, uncovered for 3 hours.
Stir once after each hour.
Divide dough into 3 greased loaf pans and let rise for 1 hour more.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: teresa's peanut butter cloud cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs, peanut butter, then flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350` for about 10 minutes.
Makes about 72 cookies.

title: caramels
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt the 1 cup butter or margarine in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt; stir thoroughly.
Stir in corn syrup.
Gradually add the sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Clip candy thermometer to side of pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat to 245° (firm ball stage).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
When cooled, cut into squares.
Wrap pieces individually in clear plastic wrap.
Makes about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: butter tasting biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine the flour, butter, and oil in food processor, fitted with steel blade.
Pulse several times to cut butter into flour.
Add buttermilk and process until well blended and mixture forms a soft sticky dough. Remove dough to a well floured surface.
Gently knead about 6 times.
Pat or roll dough to a thickness of about 1/2 inch.
Cut with a 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheesy mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done, then mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, seasoning, and onion.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2 1/2 quart buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Yield 8-10 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and add dry taco seasoning mix.
Cool at room temperature.
Mix lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Add beans, cheese, olives and hamburger mixture.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spread broccoli spears and chicken in pan.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice together.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese and stuffing mix on top with melted margarine.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: homestyle meatloaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 375 degrees for 60 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: fudge topping
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine cocoa and milk over heat.
Add stick of oleo and vanilla.
When it starts to bubble take off fire and add powdered sugar and pecans.
Pour while hot over hot cake. Work fast because topping gets hard quickly.

title: five-cup salad or easy delicious salad *
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments well, then mix all ingredients in an oblong dish and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: grape-nut custard pudding
directions: Soak cereal for 10 minutes in warm milk.
Beat eggs with fork; add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Add egg mixture to milk-cereal and stir.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a casserole dish set in a pan of hot water.
Stir twice in first 20 minutes of baking time. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, miniature marshmallows, butter and vanilla. Stir until it forms peaks.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill 30 minutes to an hour. Shape into ball and roll in crushed pecans.

title: microwave pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of 10-inch microwave-safe plate. Layer other ingredients in order given. Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken pieces in large pot with water to cover.
Add salt and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and skim off fat.
Add vegetables and garlic; cover and cook until tender.
Remove chicken and either serve separately or dice and return to soup. Season to taste.
Add rice or noodles and cook until tender. Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Add pecans. Pour in pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients together with enough buttermilk to hold mixture together like thick hush puppies.
Drop into deep hot oil by tablespoonful.
Cook until brown.

title: fire crackers
directions: Clean onions; leave green tops on them.
Spread cream cheese on the beef, then roll an onion up in the beef.

title: triple fudge cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a 2-quart saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring until pudding thickens, about 5 minutes. Add cake mix and blend until no longer lumpy.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: supper loaf
directions: Scald
milk;
cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water. Add to milk.
Cream butter and sugar;
add eggs one at a time, beating
after each.
Combine flour and salt.
Alternately add yeast, milk and flour to creamed butter and sugar. Beat until smooth.
Cover
and
let
rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Beat 25 vigorous strokes.
Spread into a well-greased tube pan.
Cover and let rise until doubled, 35 to 40 minutes. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour melted butter over chicken breasts in baking pan. Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt or Accent.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Reserve broth.
Dice chicken and mix together broth and remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish and cover with crumbled potato chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice or Chinese noodles.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all well and bake at 300°.
Spray pan (use tube pan). Start in a cold oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool on a wire rack before removing from pan.

title: oyster fritters
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Add oyster liquor, milk and eggs. Stir until well blended. Add oysters and butter.
Mix throughly. Drop from spoon into deep, hot fat and fry 4 to 6 minutes until well browned. Drain on paper towel.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In a bowl, mix pineapple and pudding; add the nuts and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 or more.

title: "beefy rice"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a deep dish casserole.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Core peppers and boil until almost tender.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Stuff peppers.
Line up in baking dish or pan.
Pour 1/2 cup water in dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour to one hour and a half.

title: mama's pumpkin pie(1972)
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle ice cream pie
directions: Mix ice cream and peanut brittle.
Pour into crust and freeze 6 hours or more.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine water, sugar, vinegar, salt, bouillon and pepper. Heat to boiling.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble.
Fry onion and pepper in 1/2 cup bacon fat until soft.
Add flour and mustard; let it bubble up 2 to 3 minutes.
Add this roux to hot water mixture; stir until smooth.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add bacon and pour over cooked, peeled warm potatoes.

title: italian delight hot dish
directions: Simmer ground beef in 3 tablespoons of oleo (or whatever you prefer) with onions and green pepper until meat is cooked.
Add cheese.
Cook spaghetti as directed.
Put all other ingredients together and add 2 cans of tomato soup.
Bake in oven at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Slice the chocolate chip rolls and put one layer on bottom of a large roasting pan.
Mix eggs, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on top of chocolate chips.
Put the other chocolate chip roll on top of cream cheese mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Put a little grease on bottom of pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange vegetable in 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish, 10 x 6 x 2. Top with chicken. Blend soup and milk together and pour over all. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: mexican wedding rings
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot, then again when cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until light.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately, beating until smooth.
Add rolled oats.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for about 12 minutes or until edges brown.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: fudge sauce(for ice cream)
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients together.
Add water and butter; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
May do in microwave.
Add vanilla.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: red velvet-pound cake
directions: Mix as any other pound cake.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix cream cheese into other ingredients with fork.
Shape into a ball with a rubber spatula.
Mix 1/2 cup chopped nuts with 2 to 3 tablespoons parsley flakes.
Roll ball in mixture; chill 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: mandarin orange delight
directions: Dissolve jello according to package directions.
Add orange slices and pineapple and set until firm.
Fold in yogurt and serve.

title: lemonade (tart)(lo-cal)
directions: Mix
all
together.
Makes an old-fashioned tart lemonade. Add
artificial
sweetener
if you like a sweeter drink. Calories per 8 ounce serving: 9.1.
Makes 3.5 quarts.

title: easy bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and mix together (use a spoon, not a mixer) until smooth. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet by teaspoon fulls. To make cookies come out better, gently mash a fork on top of them making little squares. Eat and enjoy!

title: marinated zucchini
directions: Place vegetables in a large bowl with tight-fitting cover. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Marinate in refrigerator at least 24 hours before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients; chill and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, sour cream, chopped onion, salt, pepper and soup.
Spread in 11 x 13-inch baking dish and sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Top with onion rings.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: miracle bread
directions: Mix butter, cheese, green onion, and mayonnaise together well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread on bread and toast in oven until slightly brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Line with the graham crackers. Prepare pudding with milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers and more pudding.
Finish with layer of crackers.
Put icing on top.

title: plum nutty cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Add baby food, eggs, oil and nuts. Mix well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Mix flour, nuts, brown sugar and butter.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup for topping.
Bake crust 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fruitcake squares
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix in flour, then vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in cut cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 1 hour.
Check at 45 minutes to prevent overcooking.
Yields 40 nice-size squares. Store in tightly covered container.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs in large bowl; mix well.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix and put on slow fire and let come to a boil.
Add pieces of paraffin one-inch square.
Add raw peanuts, stirring constantly, until, peanuts are parched.
Take off stove.
Add 3 teaspoons soda.
Stir just enough to mix well.
Pour out and when it gets firm, break into pieces.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oil.
Sift flour with salt and soda. Use a little flour to coat nuts and apples.
Beat remaining flours into egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Add apples and nuts.
Stir well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Bake at 275° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 1 hour. Cook oleo, brown sugar and milk to boiling.
Turn out cake.
Pour glaze over warm cake.

title: new macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain.
Melt butter; whisk in flour and cook until smooth and bubbly, about 1 minute.
Gradually whisk in milk, then add garlic, salt and peppers.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened and just beginning to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar and the Parmesan.
Stir in tortellini and parsley.
Transfer to shallow 1 1/2 quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine remaining Cheddar and bread crumbs; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Broil 4 inches from heat source for 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve with salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mash pimento with a fork until pieces are very small.
Mash the cream cheese into the pimento. Grate the Cheddar cheese and add to mixture. Add mayonnaise and a bit of mustard until the mixture is right to spread.
Sugar and salt may be added to suit taste.
Store in tight container.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and hot water.
Fold in strawberries with juice from pineapple.
Add drained pineapple, bananas and nuts all at once.
Pour 1/2 of mixture (3 cups) into a 12 x 8-inch dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread top with sour cream and gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture; chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: cottage cheese salad mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; stir well.
Mix in the rest of ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours until firm in individual or large mold.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pear-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello as usual, except use liquid from pears in place of the water.
Add cream cheese to hot liquid and beat with beaters.
Mash pears and fold in the whipped cream.
Refrigerate after placing in mold.

title: salted peanut squares
directions: Put 1/2 of nuts in an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2 pan and set aside. In microwave, melt butter and peanut butter chips on low heat. Add milk and marshmallows. Cook and stir until melted. Pour over peanuts. Sprinkle remaining peanuts on top and press firmly. (I put waxed paper on top, then press.) Cover and chill. Cut into small squares. Enjoy!!!!

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle the brisket with celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Add 2 tablespoons liquid smoke.
Wrap in foil and marinate overnight.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in a saucepan over medium-low heat.
Wrap bread in foil and heat in a 400° oven for 10 to 20 minutes.
Break into pieces for dipping.

title: nut bar
directions: Mix Crisco with flour.
Blend dry ingredients together, then add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Fold in pineapple and nuts last. Make into bar.
Bake in 350° oven 15 or 20 minutes.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Combine flour, salt and brown sugar; cut in butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Melt the chips, butter and corn syrup over low heat.
Spread mixed nuts over baked crust.
Pour melted topping over nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given; beat to moisten well. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Don't let them get too brown. Freezes well.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Form into balls. Chill. Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate. Place on wax paper. Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over slow heat.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion until tender and slightly crisp. Boil clams slightly in salted water. Remove and cook potatoes in clam water until tender, but firm. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer on low until heated; add clam juice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Just before removing from oven, top with cheese.

title: party wieners
directions: In a crock-pot combine all ingredients and simmer on high for 5 hours.
Serve hot.
Serves 10-25.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine strawberries and desired amount of glaze. Pour cheese mixture into strawberries and mix.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage in skillet.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons to saute onion, green pepper, celery and green chilies.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place bread cubes in bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Pour mixture over bread and add more cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese squares
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, layer the Jack cheese first, then Cheddar/Colby.
In a bowl, mix flour, eggs and milk, then pour evenly over cheeses.
Drop chiles on top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 20 to 25 squares.

title: relish salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.

title: bass fry
directions: Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Pour the milk into shallow dish.
Dip the fish in milk and then roll in flour.
Shake off excess flour from fish.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Gradually add sugar. Continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
No need to sift flour; measure by lightly spooning into cup and leveling off.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.

title: easy meal
directions: Moisten hands.
Flatten out biscuit.
Wrap around hot dog. Repeat steps.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: hazel's taco pie
directions: Layer 1 package crescent rolls in pizza pan.
Spread 1 package of cheese over rolls.
Cook beef and taco seasoning according to directions.
Spread beef on top of cheese.
Layer other package of cheese over beef.
Layer other package of crescent rolls on top of cheese.
Squeeze ends together and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: caramel candy
directions: Add to first mixture.
Pour into a well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate to harden.
Wrap.

title: chicken kelly
directions: In a medium size bowl, mix eggs and 1 teaspoon garlic salt. Add chicken cubes and let marinate at least two hours.
Mix bread crumbs and remaining garlic salt in a brown bag.
Add chicken and shake until chicken is thoroughly coated.
(Note:
It may be necessary to make more season mix.)
Brown chicken in oil and drain on paper towel.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Add chicken, a layer of mushrooms and cover with cheese.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and pour over casserole dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake yellow or white cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bring to a rolling boil the sugar and milk; pour over cake.
Combine Cool Whip and coconut.
Spread over cake.
Chill. This makes a very moist cake.

title: sage dressing for chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, parsley, onions, sage and chicken broth. Mix until moistened to hold together.
Stuff loosely into chicken and close.
Place breast side up in a roasting pan.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise.
Put broccoli, then chicken cutlets in a casserole dish.
Pour soup mix over all.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: jello no bake cake
directions: Cut or tear angel food cake into large pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together jello and boiling water in large bowl. Mix in strawberries and cold water and pour over angel food cake. Top with Cool Whip when jello is set.
Great for a refreshing summer cake.

title: easy pineapple pie
directions: Mix the pineapple, vanilla pudding (dry) and sour cream. Pour into cooled pie shell. Top with cool whip and refrigerate. It is so good and so easy.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove tops, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Brown meat in skillet; cook with onion.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in rice, tomato and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Fill peppers with meat mixture, topping with remaining cheese.
Arrange in 9-inch square baking dish.
Add 1/4 cup water to pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until peppers are tender.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in a bowl the flour, salt and alum.
Bring to a boil the water, oil and food coloring.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix; knead.
Store in airtight container.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins until a fork can be inserted, but do not overcook.
Remove skins and cut in quarters. Place in a large casserole dish.

title: louisiana red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and add about 3 cups of water to beans.
Add all ingredients to beans and cook on medium fire for about 1 1/2 hours or until beans can be mashed or cooked thoroughly.
If too dry at any time, add a cup of water, plus 1/2 cup of oil.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet over medium-high heat, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add skinned, boneless chicken breast and brown.
Add soup, water and vegetable combination.
Heat to boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serves 4.

title: grilled flounder with olive butter
directions: Puree butter, lemon juice and olives.
Season flounder with salt and pepper.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes per side; place each serving on plate.
Top with 2 tablespoons of olive butter.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix Wesson oil, sugar and eggs; beat until smooth.
Slowly sift in flour, soda, salt and baking powder, mixing thoroughly, at moderate speed.
Add vanilla, 1 cup pecans (optional) and coarsely chopped apples.
Bake in greased and floured pan, at 350°, for about 1 hour or until done.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Simmer until done, 20 minutes.
Refrigerate; drain before serving.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup additional cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: oatmeal cocoa chippers
directions: Preheat oven
In a small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking
soda
and
salt;
set
aside.
In a large mixer bowl, combine
margarine,
brown
sugar, granulated sugar and vanilla extract;
beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after
each
addition.
Gradually
beat in flour mixture. Stir
in
chocolate bits, oats and walnuts.
Drop by slightly rounded
tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to
11 minutes
for chewy cookies and 12 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from a cookie sheet; cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Layer in casserole. Add vegetable layer, then chopped onion (if desired).
Salt.
Spread mushroom soup over vegetables.
Rinse can with 1/3 cup water and pour over. Top with Tater Tots and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: viener schnitzel
directions: Pound veal until 1/4 inch thick.
Dredge with mixture of flour, Season-All, pepper and nutmeg.
Dip in mixture of egg and water, then into bread crumbs.
Let dry 30 minutes.
Brown veal on both sides in 1/2 cup of butter, cooking about 15 minutes. Remove veal to hot platter.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Place in preheated 350° oven.
Cook for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Center will puff up, but become firm when done.

title: chile pie
directions: Layer baking dish, starting with Fritos and ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add chilies, pinto beans, kidney beans, corn, hominy, Ro-Tel tomatoes, chopped tomatoes and beef broth (all undrained).
Add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing mixes.
Bring to a boil, simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: cranberry salad(diabetic)
directions: Grind the cranberries while frozen.
Grind up apple.
Dissolve jello in the hot water.
Cool, then combine other ingredients and refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna salad
directions: Toast oats in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: fruited chicken
directions: In plastic or paper bag, mix the 3/4 cup flour, salt, celery salt, garlic salt and nutmeg.
Shake chicken pieces, a few at a time, in flour mixture until coated.
In large skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Brown chicken on all sides.
Place chicken in 13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup syrup.
Sprinkle pineapple over chicken.
Stir the 3 tablespoons flour and the sugar into butter remaining in skillet. Add reserved pineapple syrup and soy sauce; cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Spoon evenly over chicken and pineapple.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jane's taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream and taco mix.
Spread on serving tray.
Top with ground beef, chopped tomatoes, chopped lettuce, Cheddar cheese and black olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Pour over cooked popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheese vegetables
directions: Mix onion, vegetables and water chestnuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt together 1/2 stick butter and Cheez Whiz.
Pour over vegetables.
Crush crackers and spread over vegetables.
Melt 1 stick of butter and pour over the crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dolly parton cake
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into a 9-inch square pan.
Cook in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing until blended.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust; chill.
Prepare chocolate pudding by package directions.
Spread over cream cheese layer; chill. Prepare vanilla pudding by package directions.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Chill.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Cut into squares.

title: pink parfait
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello with small amount boiling water (about 1/4 cup).
Add about 1 cup ice cubes to hot liquid and stir until all ice cubes become very small (will not completely melt) and liquid becomes cold and thick.
Scoop ice cubes out with spoon (that has holes).
Whip in Cool Whip until mixture is pink and fluffy.
Add cut-up strawberries and fill 1/2 cup container with fluffy mixture.
Refrigerate.
When semi-stiff, top with whole strawberry.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, and drain leaving a little water in them.
Mash the potatoes and set aside.
Combine the rest of the ingredients together and add to the mashed potatoes in small amounts, mixing well as you go.
Put party potatoes into a baking dish and dot the top with chives and butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix well.
May be sloppy.
Pour over the cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: tomatoes and macaroni
directions: Cook onion & pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt, & pepper.
Add tomatoes; cook till slightly thickened and bubbly.
Pour over cooked macaroni or shells and stir.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: saucy flounder
directions: In skillet, melt butter. Add onion and saute 1 minute. Lay thawed fish on top of onion. Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes. Add seasonings and tomatoes. Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes.

title: soap finger paint
directions: Beat with an eggbeater until mixture is thick.
Color with a few drops of food coloring. This is a great sensory activity.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Mix hearts, mayonnaise, cheese
and garlic powder together.
Put in Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Put pineapple and vanilla pudding mix in bowl and stir.
Add sour cream and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) baked pie shells.
Refrigerate and chill 3 hours.
Delicious and easy!

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, milk and salt in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a hard boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper; let stand until cool.

title: sweet potato-pumpkin pie
directions: Cream potatoes and pumpkin well.
Add sugars, butter, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: bacon sausage roll ups
directions: Cut bacon strips into thirds.
If small sausages are not available, cut large sausages into 2-inch pieces.
Wrap bacon around each sausage and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Fill a 9 x 13 inch pan with roll ups.
Sprinkle roll ups with brown sugar. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat cream of broccoli-chicken soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine and add onions, celery and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat all ingredients with mixer or by hand until smooth.
Put in graham cracker pie crust and chill for 2 to 4 hours.
If large pie crust is used (10-inch), use 10 ounce Cool Whip and a little more juice (not too much).

title: easy lemon chicken
directions: In skillet, brown chicken in 2 tablespoons vegetable oil. Pour off fat.
Add gravy, lemon and vegetables.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Serves 6.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, chives and salt until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cooking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put melted butter in oblong pan.
Then mix flour, sugar, egg and milk.
Then pour over butter.
Then mix peaches and water and spread over mixture.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: chitterlings
directions: Wash chitterlings in
warm
water, rubbing as you would clothes, to remove	all grease and residue.
Strip as much fat as possible from
each
piece	and
wash
in clear cold water. Drain and wash
again
holding
each
piece under cold running water (chitterlings
must
be
thoroughly
cleaned).
Place in large pot, cover with
water and bring to a boil, drain, cover with fresh
water.
Add	remaining
ingredients.
Cook covered over medium heat until
done,
about 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Drain, cut into small pieces and serve with hot sauce.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Take 3 slices of bread at a time and trim crusts.
(Works best if bread is slightly frozen.)
Spread mayonnaise between slices.	Cut each stack of 3 into 9 pieces. Frost the sides and top with cheese mixture.
Freeze on a cookie sheet until hard.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Yields approximately 50 cheese puffs.

title: microwave nacho dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and refried beans together.
Layer picante sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.

title: crockpot macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni. Grease crockpot and layer macaroni, cheese and margarine. Salt and pepper each layer. Mix milk and beaten eggs. Pour mixture over layers. Top with cheese and sprinkle with paprika. Cook 3 to 4 hours on low setting. Do not open or stir during cooking time.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Slice eggs over chicken.
Pour peas over eggs.
Blend soup and broth until creamy.
Pour over chicken, eggs, peas, salt and pepper to taste.
Blend flour, milk and melted margarine and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix sugar and butter in a heavy pan.
Allow to remain over fire until sugar is dissolved and is a golden brown in color.
Chop nuts up fine.
Put a layer of nuts, then Hershey bars.
Pour hot mixture over this and repeat the Hershey bars and nuts.
Allow to cool overnight and break up in small pieces.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin until fluffy and smooth.
Mix flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda with mixture thoroughly.
Spread batter in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Cut into bars.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: barbecued spareribs and sauce
directions: Heat in separate pan.
Use regular pork ribs.
If you use country-style ribs, cook them first to remove grease, then put them in the pan with the sauce over and follow same directions.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine beef, eggs, oatmeal, salt, pepper and parsley flakes. Roll and form bite-sized meatballs. Brown in large skillet and drain on paper towels. Mix remaining ingredients to make sauce. Add meatballs to sauce and simmer for 1/2 hour. Makes 70-80 meatballs.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan with oil or spray. Sprinkle with sugar. Mix all other ingredients together. Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: stu's gazpacho
directions: Finely chop all vegetables (a food processor is ideal for this).
Combine with all remaining ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours (makes 6 cups).
Serve this soup chilled in bowls with one of the following garnishes; chives, croutons or nonfat sour cream.

title: macay fajitas
directions: Marinade:
Combine salt, pepper, lime juice, garlic and olive oil.
Put meat in marinade and set aside for 1 hour.

title: easy skillet macaroni and beef
directions: Lightly brown beef in skillet; remove from heat.
Cook macaroni, onion and green pepper in meat fat until onion is soft. (If meat fat is not sufficient to prevent sticking, add Wesson corn oil.)
Return meat to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes, or until macaroni is cooked to suit your taste.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add chicken.
Let stand approximately 1/2 hour.
Roll chicken in breadcrumbs.
Brown in skillet using margarine or oil. Drain on paper towel.
Once browned and drained, place chicken in casserole dish.
Add cheese and broth.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Serve with rice; enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage fine and boil until tender in salted water. Drain.
Wilt onion in butter.
When wilted, add cheese in chunks and allow to melt over low heat.
Add soup to cheese mixture. When blended, add boiled cabbage and mix well.
Add crumbs, about 3/4 to 1 cup.
Salt and pepper if desired.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: weight watcher chicken
directions: Place chicken in single layer in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave magic muffins(6 muffins; cooking time 2 to 3 minutes)
directions: In large, shallow microwave-safe dish or glass pie plate, arrange chicken cutlets in a single layer.
In small bowl, stir together 1/2 cup broth, the onion, thyme and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Microwave, uncovered, on High (100%) 2 minutes. Rearrange cutlets so outside edges are in center.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes longer or until chicken is cooked through and no pink spots remain.
With slotted spatula, remove cutlets to warm serving platter or individual plates, reserving cooking liquid.

title: chocolate glazed brownies
directions: Prepare and bake One Bowl Brownies as directed.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in medium microwavable bowl on High for 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in corn syrup and milk until well blended.
Spread over brownies.
Let stand 1 hour.
Garnish with large walnut pieces.

title: turkey cheddar casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions on the box.
Add minced onions to boiling water.
Fluff rice and spread in greased, 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with peas and cover with turkey.
Blend soup and milk together and pour evenly over turkey. Combine crackers and butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: karen's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix salt, cinnamon, ginger and cloves in small bowl.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in pumpkin and sugar - spice mixture. Gradually stir in eggnog.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated oven at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350 degrees:
bake 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 1 hour.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco together and beat well.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix baking soda with buttermilk.
Add flour and roll out.
Don't make too stiff at first.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in one large bowl with wooden spoon until moist.
Pour into one large loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or 2 small loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lay tortilla chips on cookie sheet. Mix onion in with salsa.
Pour a small amount on each chip. Sprinkle cheese over chips.
Bake for approximately 5 minutes or until the cheese has melted.

title: p.b.  and c.
directions: Take 2 parts of unselfishness.
Add 1 part patience and work together.
Add plenty of industry.
Lighten with good spirits and sweeten with kindness.
Put in smiles as thick as raisins in plum pudding.
Bake by the warmth with streams from a loving heart.
If this fails to make a good day, the fault is not with the recipe but with the cook!

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Prepare crumb topping.
Combine flour, sugar and Crisco and mix until it resembles coarse meal.
Set aside.

title: pineapple fluff mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake in 4 layers or 2 thick layers and split.

title: pizza fruit pie all-star recipe
directions: Mix together cake mix and oil and pat into a large pizza pan. Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs until running smooth. Add milk and beat well. Dissolve sugar in boiling water. Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and beat.
Dice bread and place in loaf pan. Add raisins and pour egg mixture over all to soak bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Place in pan of warm water and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 or 1 1/2 hours until firm.

title: vanilla wafer banana pudding
directions: Scald milk in top of double boiler over direct heat.
Mix egg yolks with sugar until creamy.
Add salt and flour.
Add slowly to milk.
Stir until right consistency.
Add vanilla.
Layer wafers, bananas, sauce and repeat.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add
1/4 c. sugar to egg whites, bake until meringue is browned.

title: holiday cashews
directions: Combine cashews and butter.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes. Stir in spice.
Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Add raisins and toss to coat.
Spread on foil to cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, brown sugar, sugar and butter; blend together until crumbly.
Place apples in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Top with oatmeal mixture; sprinkle with salt and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in yogurt mixture and roll in dry mixture.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: salmon party log
directions: Peel and core slice pears. Weigh the fruit and use 1 pound fruit with 3/4 pound sugar.
Put pears in clear water and boil gently until tender and can be pierced with a fork.
Take from water and put a layer of pears and a layer of sugar.
Repeat until all has been used.
Let stand overnight.
Pour off syrup, bring to a boil, add pears and cook until clear and the syrup is thick as preserve syrup.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat sweet potatoes, eggs and sugar until well combined. Beat in milk, orange juice, honey, vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 to 55 minutes, until knife or toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Set oven to 400°.
For the pastry, roll into a circle and line a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Scoop the flesh out of the pumpkin and throw away the skin and seeds.
Put in a pan and cover with water; simmer for 25 minutes.
Drain away the water and leave the pumpkin to cool down. Mash with a fork or in a blender until it's perfectly smooth and free of lumps.
Beat pumpkin, eggs, cream, salt, sugar and spices.

title: pecan praline squares
directions: Dissolve sugar in Pet milk and bring to a boil. Add butter and pecans. Cook until syrup reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes without stirring. Beat until slightly thickened. Pour into greased pan; let stand until room temperature. Cut into squares.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pour rice evenly over bottom of buttered, 2-quart oblong dish. Sprinkle herbs over rice.
Mix soups, margarine, sherry and milk. Pour small amount over rice to moisten.
Sprinkle with sliced mushrooms.
Top with chicken.
Pour remainder of soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and almonds.
Bake in an uncovered dish at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat.
Add taco mix, water and olives.
Simmer.
Put biscuits, flattened out, on cookie sheet.
Cover with meat.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove.
Cover with corn chips, cheese, lettuce and tomatoes; cut and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: Fry meat; drain.
Add seasoning as meat fries.
Add cans of corn, tomatoes and beans.
Bring to boil.
Add more salt and chili powder to taste.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with Mexican corn bread.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Heat apple cider.
Add brown sugar, stirring until dissolved. Make a bag for spices using any porous material such as cheesecloth.
Put bag of spices in cider and simmer 15 to 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag and serve.
Makes 8 cups.

title: kraut balls
directions: I didn't have potatoes, so I substituted rice.

title: grape jelly
directions: To make jelly, measure juice and sugar.
Combine and cook over high heat, stirring constantly until heavy steam escapes from juice.
Do not boil.
Pour in cans and seal.

title: macaroni skillet dinner
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
In a heavy skillet, brown onion in oil.
Add meat and cook until lightly browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni and cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until celery and green pepper are tender.
Stir in macaroni and cook 10 minutes longer.
Garnish with cheese.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter until it looks like meal. Sprinkle 1/4 of this in baked pie shell.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick and pour into crust.
Top with meringue and sprinkle rest of peanut butter and sugar mixture on top; brown in oven.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Fry and crumble sausage in skillet.
When done, add water, then soup.
Stir and simmer about 15 minutes.

title: coconut-caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add coconut and chopped pecans.
Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand Milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture in each cooled pastry shells.
Drizzle 1/4 of the caramel topping on each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 of the coconut mixture evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients making sure you finish with the coconut mixture on top.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let frozen pie stand at room temperature 5 minute before slicing.
Cut small pieces - very rich, but very delicious.

title: grandma oakley's jelly cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and jelly.
Slowly add dry ingredients, then milk and vanilla flavoring.
Bake 3 layers for about 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: turnips and red peppers
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy skillet. Add the peppers, turnips and garlic. Stir-fry over medium heat, adding more butter if needed, until the turnips are tender when pierced with a knife. Season with salt and pepper.

title: havreflarn (swedish lace wafers)
directions: Sift together in a bowl the flour, baking powder and sugar. Add oats, heavy cream, corn syrup, oleo and vanilla; mix well. Drop on ungreased sheet 4 inches apart using 1/4 teaspoon as measure.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove carefully to waxed paper to cool.
Makes approximately 6 dozen 2-inch wafers.

title: reindeer stew(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large cooking pot, bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes the meat with water, tomatoes and onion.
Add potatoes; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes with rice if desired.
Add noodles or macaroni; simmer until done, 10 minutes or more.
Just before serving, add vegetable soup.

title: fluffy pineapple pie
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar
and
salt.	Add pineapple juice and blend. Cook
over
low heat until thick, stirring constantly. Add
a little hot mixture to beaten egg;
stir into remaining hot mixture.
Cook
until thick.
Add marshmallows;
stir and add pineapple.	Chill
1 hour, then fold in whipped cream and pour into
an 8-inch pie pan lined with vanilla wafers.	Chill or freeze.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Mix margarine, hot sauce and vinegar.
Arrange wings on broiler pan.
Brush wings with sauce.
Roast for 25 minutes in 450° oven.
Turn wings.
Brush with sauce
Roast for 20 minutes.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water in bowl.
Let stand about 10 minutes. Add 2 cups flour, salt and oil. Beat until smooth. Gradually stir in more flour (about 1/2 cup) to form soft dough. Turn dough out to floured surface.
Knead until smooth and elastic, adding more flour (up to 1/2 cup) if necessary to prevent dough from being too sticky.
Place dough in a greased bowl. Cover and let stand to rise about double (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Prepare jello.
Let thicken slightly.
Grind cranberries, oranges, apples and celery.
Mix together with salt and sugar. Mix into the thickened jello.
Let stand several hours.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix well.
Make into small balls.
Place in single layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hairy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except dried beef.
Chill 3 hours.
Roll into a ball.
Roll cheese ball in dried beef to coat.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Make 3 wells in the dry ingredients.
In the first well add the vanilla; in the second well add the vinegar; in the third add the oil.
Pour the cold water over all the ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. When the cake is cool remove it from the pan and frost with Buttercream Icing.

title: polish pizza
directions: Mix the dry ingredients with the shortening.
Combine eggs and sour cream.
Mix dry and wet ingredients together.
Shape into large jelly roll pan. Top with pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb fine.
Mix with sugar and remaining ingredients. Let stand a few minutes.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.
Place meringue on top.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, place frozen strawberries, bananas, peaches and pineapple.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over fruit.
Mix well. Allow fruit to thaw in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: coconut hummingbird cake
directions: Butter and flour three 9-inch round cake pans.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add eggs and vegetable oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in banana, pineapple with juice, pecans and vanilla. Divide batter evenly among cake pans.
Bake until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean (25 to 30 minutes at 350°). Cool 10 minutes, then invert onto wire rack and cool completely. Place on cake layer or cake plate.
Cover with frosting and repeat with remaining layers.
Cover sides of cake with remaining frosting.
Sprinkle coconut cake over top and sides.
Enjoy!

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into crock-pot (heaping full). Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon, salt and cloves over apples.
Cover and begin on high until the apples begin to settle.
Then turn to low and cook all day or until thick and dark.
Stir occasionally. Whip when done.
Freeze in containers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients for filling.
Spoon into pie crust.
Cover with top crust.
Brush with egg.
Slit top crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix oatmeal, coconut, flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown (time varies depending on size of balls).
Yield:
approximately 48 cookies.

title: peanut butter blossom cookies
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls.
Roll in sugar and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
As soon as the cookies come out of the oven, place a Hershey Kiss in the center of each.

title: lemon cake bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Grease (not oil) and lightly flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans. In large bowl, blend sugar, lemon peel and oil. Beat 1 minute at medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in remaining ingredients just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour batter into prepared pans. Bake at 325° for 50 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan. If desired, glaze with lemon glaze. Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli with rigatoni
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil, butter and garlic, gently, until pan gets very hot.
Add chicken broth.
Add broccoli.
Cover. Simmer just until broccoli is al dente.
Add half the fresh basil and the drained, hot rigatoni (cooked al dente) to the skillet; mix thoroughly.
Put in a hot serving dish and sprinkle with parsley, pepper, grated cheese and remaining basil.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch glass pan.
Mix all of the ingredients except crumbs and the margarine together.
Top with crumbs mixed with the softened margarine.
Spread evenly over the top of the pudding.
Dust sparingly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° until it bubbles.

title: jello pie
directions: Freeze evaporated milk in bowl until ice crystals begin to form in milk.
Whip until stiff.
In medium saucepan, mix together sugar, eggs and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved.
Mix in the whipped milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, flaked coconut and chopped pecans.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup.
Bring just to boil over medium-high heat.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Fold in Rice Krispies a little at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 3/4 bag of each kind of chips in microwave and pour over Rice Krispie mixture.

title: oyster confetti rice
directions: Drain oysters; reserve 1 tablespoon liquid.
Brown pork in oil.
Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute.
Add reserved oyster liquid and remaining ingredients except zucchini.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add zucchini, then oysters.
Heat through and serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put in greased 2 quart casserole in order given. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate teddy bears
