directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla in a large bowl. Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to the butter mixture and blend.
Chill until dough is firm enough to handle.
To shape teddy bears:

Form a portion of dough into a large ball for body (1-inch), 1 medium ball for head, 4 small balls for arms and legs (1/2-inch), 2 smaller balls for ears, 1 tiny ball for nose and 4 tiny balls for paws.

title: peanut butter pudding
directions: Beat whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Set aside. Mix peanut butter, pudding, coconut and milk.
Fold in topping and chill.

title: baked fish with dill flavor
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the fish in a baking dish and sprinkle with tomatoes, onion, dill, salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until the fish is tender and flaky.
Serve hot, garnished with dill sprigs and tomato wedges. Serves 4.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Put coffee and creamer in a blender and blend for a few seconds. Put cocoa mix in and blend a little more. Put in a container large enough to shake. Add other ingredients and shake well together. Do not blend. Add 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: mom's caramel nuts
directions: Cook sugars, Milnot and syrup to a soft ball, 236° on candy thermometer.
Cool to 110°.
Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it starts to lose its gloss.
Add nuts and coat.

title: spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef.
Drain beef and put in a heavy boiler.
Cook onion in beef fat until tender; drain.
Add onion to ground beef.
If using store bought tomatoes, remove cores and cut up.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients to the ground beef and onion.
Let simmer for 30 minutes longer.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Skin, bone and cut chicken into large pieces. Saute onion and green pepper in a little margarine.
Mix onion and green pepper with the chicken, 2 cans of soup and Ro-Tel.
Heat thoroughly. On the bottom of a large casserole dish, put a layer of tortillas, that have been cut into strips and dipped in chicken broth.
Over this, layer half of the chicken mix and half of the cheese. Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken broth over all.
Add another layer of tortillas, chicken mix, broth and cheese. Reserve a little cheese to sprinkle on top after cooking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add eggs and milk.
Pour mixture into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: dried beef cheese spread
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Combine with cottage cheese.
Add olives, onion and the sauces.
Mix well.
Shape into big ball.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate.
To serve, roll ball in rest of beef.

title: crazy bread
directions: In a bowl dissolve yeast into water.
Mix in sugar and salt. Add flour, cup by cup.
Mix well and knead for 5 to 7 minutes. Roll onto cookie sheet, brush with 1/4 cup melted butter and sprinkle with garlic powder and Parmesan cheese. Cut into slices with a pizza cutter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together, adding eggs one at a time. Bake in 3 layers, greased and floured well, using temperature setting on cake mix box.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown onions and peppers in small amount of fat.
Remove from pan; drain.
Brown meat, seasoned with chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper, in same skillet.
Cook macaroni; drain.

title: beef roll
directions: Mix well; set in refrigerator for 3 days.
Each day, stir for 5 minutes, trying to mix as well as you can.

title: two cup pineapple cake
directions: Mix together. Pour in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Icing while warm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean or until pie seems firm in the middle.
Usually 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes with broccoli and cheese
directions: Place 1/2 of potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Add 1/2 of the onion.
Sift 1/2 of the flour; sprinkle half seasoning and add handful of broccoli.
Repeat layers.
Melt cheese with 1/2 cup milk and add remaining 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over potatoes.
If cheesier flavor is desired, add more cheese and place between layers of potatoes.
(Optional:
Sprinkle top with fine dry bread crumbs.)
Bake covered 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then bake uncovered an additional 15 minutes.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Add salt, sugar and water to egg white.
Blend mix and add pecans.
Mix well.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes in 250° oven.
Stir twice during cooking time.

title: best ever stuffed peppers
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine raw ground beef, 1 can tomato sauce, diced onion, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Mix thoroughly; set aside.
Cut top off of bell peppers and remove seeds.
Blanch for 1 to 2 minutes in boiling water.
Place peppers in 9-inch cake pan.
Stuff with meat mixture.
Cover with tin foil and bake at 350°, checking for doneness after 1 hour.
It will probably take an additional half hour.
Heat remaining can of tomato sauce. Pour over peppers and serve with rice.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell, about 1 hour at 325°.

title: mom's lemon squares
directions: Mix together and press half of mixture firmly and evenly in bottom of slightly greased 8 x 8 pan.

title: edwardian english muffins
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water (use warm water for dry yeast). Pour scalded milk over sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm. Beat in egg and 1 cup flour.
Add softened yeast and cornmeal. Stir in more flour to make a soft dough.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan. Layer pecans and coconut in bottom of pan. Mix cake by package directions and pour over pecan/coconut layer. Mix softened oleo and softened cream cheese until smooth. Add powdered sugar and beat until smooth. Drop mixture by spoonfuls over the cake mix. DO NOT SPREAD! Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried steak
directions: Wash steaks.
Place steaks in shallow pan.
Season with garlic salt and black pepper.
Sprinkle with minced garlic and onion. Cover steaks and marinate in refrigerator about 30 minutes before frying.
Heat oil in frying pan to medium heat.
Fry steaks with a share of onion rings, until browned.
Serves 4.

title: magic bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle crumbs over butter. Press together to make a crust.
Layer coconut and chocolate chips.
Top evenly with milk. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Take out of oven and cut into bars.
Let cool a little, then take out of pan and place on serving dish to cool completely.

title: bean soup
directions: Cover beans with water and soak 15 hours in a cool place.
Add meat, onion and pepper; bring to boiling.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours or until beans are mushy.
Remove meat and cut into small pieces.
Press remaining ingredients through a sieve or food mill; add meat.
Add boiling water for consistency, if necessary.
Salt to taste.
Pour hot into hot jars leaving 1-inch headspace.
Adjust caps, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Process pints 1 hour and 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar with peaches and pour into casserole pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and egg; spread over the peaches. Melt oleo; drizzle over top.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: eclair cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat margarine and water until it comes to a boil.

Remove from heat. Gradually add flour and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spread in greased 12 x 15 cookie sheet that has raised sides. Bake for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour and salt. Stir in milk.
Cook until bubbly and stir for 2 minutes. Stir a portion of the hot mixture into egg yolks. Add to remaining hot mixture.
Return to heat for 2 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust. Spread with a basic meringue and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt; boil 7 minutes.
Stir constantly; set off heat.
Add nuts, chocolate kisses and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper.
Makes about 6 pounds.

title: "not fried" onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings.
Dip rings into yogurt, then into bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: fried rice and chicken
directions: Cook rice; stir-fry with onion in skillet with oil.
Put in cooked chicken.
Cut up green onion.
Put in rice and chicken. Stir.
Drop egg in middle and stir.
Add sauce; bring to boil and serve.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Before you start prepare all the above ingredients. Place cracked wheat in a large bowl, add boiling water and set aside to soak for 15 minutes. Place chopped parsley, mint, onions and tomatoes in a large bowl then add the salt and pepper. Now mix all your ingredients thoroughly. Drain the cracked wheat, squeeze out excess water and add to the bowl and combine. Finally, add lemon juice, olive oil and mix all ingredients. Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: hot sandwiches
directions: Combine all the ingredients together in large bowl.
Put into buns.
Wrap in foil and heat about 1/2 hour at 250°.

title: cinnamon streusel coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine salad oil, egg and milk; sift together dry ingredients.
Add to milk mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Spicy Topping. Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: pink parfait punch
directions: Dilute juices according to directions on can and mix in a large punch bowl.
About 10 minutes before serving, combine strawberry ice cream and 1/2 gallon of the vanilla ice cream. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and float the other 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream on top.
Makes 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, leaving a small amount of cheese and cracker crumbs to put on top.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; form loaves (4 to 5).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Pour into large greased casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Should have a golden yellow top when done.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Combine chopped dates, water and sugar.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add broken nuts.
Cool.
Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add vanilla, beaten egg and flour mixture.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, relish, onion, parsley, pimento and lemon juice.
Cover and chill for several hours. Serve with fish or seafood.
Makes slightly more than two cups.

title: cinnamon apple jelly(a perfect christmas gift)
directions: Combine cider, pectin and candy in a large pot.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Pour into jelly glasses and seal.

title: lil' smokies
directions: Brown Lil' Smokies in large frypan.
Remove from pan and place on paper towel to dry up some of the grease.
Cut biscuits in halves or in fourths depending on how much bread you desire with each sausage.
Follow cooking instructions on biscuit cans. Preheat oven.
Wrap each sausage with biscuit and place on cookie sheet or baking pan.
Bake sausage and biscuits until done and golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Serve with honey mustard sauce or your favorite sauce.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water; set aside.
Add flour, sugar, Crisco, soda, eggs and buttermilk.
Mix good with your hands.
Roll out thin when ready to bake.
Cut out with round cookie cutter, flour, double over, let set for five minutes and bake.
Best to let dough set in refrigerator overnight, then cut out and bake.
Bake in a 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore supreme
directions: It's best to precook chicken for about 30 minutes, either roasting

title: chocolate puffs
directions: Add water to shortening, sugar and cocoa; beat until sugar dissolves.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with combined egg, sour cream and vanilla.
Fill greased cupcake pans half full; bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallow half before baking or frost with seven minute frosting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: barley vegetable soup
directions: Bring 5 cups water to boil with salt in large saucepan.
Add tomatoes, barley, bay leaf, sage and oregano.
Reduce heat, cover pan and simmer until barley is tender, 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; break in bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, sour cream and soup together.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Put crackers on top of chicken mixture.
Pour melted butter and poppy seed over cracker crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: beef and potatoes with rosemary(makes 8 servings)
directions: Arrange potatoes and carrots in 3 1/2 to 6-quart slow cooker. Trim excess fat from beef.
Mix mustard, rosemary, thyme, salt and pepper; spread evenly over beef.
Place beef in cooker. Sprinkle onion over beef.
Pour broth evenly over beef and vegetables.
Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 10 hours or until beef and vegetables are tender.
Remove beef and vegetables from cooker, using slotted spoon; place on serving platter.
Skim fat from beef juices in cooker if desired.
Serve beef with juices.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt bark; add chocolate chips and stir until dissolved.
Add vanilla and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: shrimp loaf
directions: Combine shrimp, onion, Tabasco sauce, lemon juice and cream cheese in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape into a loaf and chill. Before serving, pour cocktail sauce over loaf.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon pies
directions: Prepare crust; crush enough wafers to cover the bottom of two pie pans.
Place whole wafers around the sides.
In a large bowl, mix well 3 cans condensed milk and 6 egg yolks, then add 3/4 cup of fresh lemon juice.
When mixture starts to thicken, spoon it into the two pie crusts.
Try to divide it equally.
Beat egg whites until they are foamy; add sugar slowly.
Beat until stiff.
Spoon over pie and bake until brown.
Bake at 325° until meringue is brown.

title: sunday dinner chicken
directions: Crumble
cornbread
and
set
aside.
Saute
celery and onion. Mix bread, onion, celery, chicken broth, chicken soup, chicken and rice soup, salt and pepper.
Grease 3 quart baking dish and put half of the mix in baking dish.
Spread and cover with chicken; then cover chicken with the remaining mix.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: You may use any fruit desired.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Blend the margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Mix the baking powder and cracker crumbs.
Add the pecans, coconut and Carnation milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: glorified pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops until brown.
Set aside.
Drain off fat.
In skillet combine soup and water; return chops to skillet.
Cover. Cook over low heat 15 minutes or until chops are no longer pink, stirring often.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Place unpeeled potatoes in large saucepan.
Add water to cover. Boil 20 minutes or until tender.
Peel and slice.
Turn into serving dish.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Leave drippings in pan. Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Add onion to skillet.
Saute until tender.
Add beer, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss lightly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Allow the butter to get real soft.
Add other ingredients and beat until thoroughly blended.
Fold in pecans, as many as wanted (2 cups).
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: best coconut cake
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat eggs in, one at a time.
Add flavoring. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well after each addition. Mix until well blended.
Spread batter evenly in three greased 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and frost with Seven Minute Frosting.

title: buster-bars
directions: Combine crushed Oreo cookies and melted butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with peanuts and spread softened ice cream over this.
Chill.
Mix and boil 8 minutes, stirring constantly, the remaining ingredients.
Cool and spread over ice cream and freeze.
Cut in 3-inch squares.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Boil but do not overcook potatoes.
Cool and coarsely grate. Melt butter and cheese and stir in sour cream.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt
marshmallows
in	microwave.
Mix all ingredients and pack
into	graham cracker box.
Keep refrigerated.
Line the box with waxed paper (a loaf pan works just as well).

title: *apple pie*
directions: Cut apples up in pie shell.
Put 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and margarine together. Put over apples.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: grilled onions
directions: Peel and cut ends off onions.
Cook on grill until black and spewing or well done.
Peel off black and cut an x halfway through.
Put in 1/4 of margarine and sprinkle with lemon pepper and paprika.
Serve warm.
Great with meat cooked on grill!

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, saute the bacon until crisp.
Add green onions and potatoes.
Saute for a few minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add clam juice or milk; stir to blend well.
Bring to boil.
Simmer, stirring, until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Finally add clams with liquid and whipping cream.
Heat soup, stirring, just until simmering.
Do not boil or clams will toughen.
Sprinkle with parsley or basil leaves.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: macaroni - rosamarina salad
directions: Mix eggs, flour, salt and sugar and add to fruit juices and cook until pudding thickness.
Chill until very cold.
Mix together macaroni, fruit, pudding and Cool Whip.
Add a few drops of vanilla.
Serve cold.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Mold into small balls and bake at 350° until done (15 to 20 minutes).

title: corned beef
directions: Put the corned beef in a large pot and cover with water. Bring to a boil and add spices to taste.
Reduce to a strong simmer and add 1 tsp. Soy sauce, 1-1/2 tsp. Worcestershire, and a can of beer; mix well and cover.
Add carrots,
potatoes and cabbage wedges for the last hour of cooking.

title: potato party
directions: Scrub potatoes; rub lightly with oil and pierce with fork. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Serve with following toppings:

title: lemony loaf bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. In another bowl, whisk together the egg, egg whites, yogurt, oil and lemon peel. Add to the dry ingredients; stir just until moistened. Fold in the berries. Transfer to a greased 8 x 4 loaf pan. Bake in 350° oven for an hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool for 10 to 12 minutes before removing from pan.

title: bag-a-deerwaterford, michigan
directions: Marinate meat in Italian dressing in bag and leave in refrigerator overnight.
Remove excess dressing and add 1 Tbsp. flour to mixture and shake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix thawed broccoli and melted butter and soup together.
Add herb stuffing until moistened and all liquid is absorbed.
Bake in 2 to 2 1/2-quart dish at 350° for approximately 45 to 60 minutes or until slightly browned and bubbly.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add taco mix and chili powder.
Put into crock-pot.
Add peppers and cheese.
Let melt.
Leave crock-pot on low and stir.
Serve hot.

title: mom's easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and sour cream in a large bowl.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: vegetable batter
directions: Combine oil, egg, water, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt in mixer bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Use to coat vegetables for frying.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
While vegetables are hot, add margarine, soup and sour cream.
Mix and add 1 cup stuffing mix and grated cheese.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown sausage and drain well. Saute onion and celery in a small amount of grease.
Combine other ingredients, stirring gently.
Add sausage.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour or until rice in center is done. Serves 5.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and soup mix.
Form a ball and roll in pecans.
Then chill.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients plus salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: flat apple pie
directions: Make dough with first 5 ingredients.
Divide in half and roll out the first one to fit a 12 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Cover with corn flakes, then with apples, then with sugar.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with cinnamon and then top with rolled out second ball of dough.
Brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: huntington chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in broth reserved from chicken until tender.
Mix chicken, noodles, vegetables and cheese.
Mix together with enough broth to keep from being dry.
Add soup and pimento.
Put in large casserole dish or divide in two dishes. Top with parsley flakes and more cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Cream the cottage cheese.
Add jello and beat.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add drained fruit.

title: johnny rosetti
directions: Saute meat; add chopped ingredients and steam until done.
Add the other ingredients, except the olives and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Place some olives on top to form a rosette.
(Any arrangement that resembles the shape of a rose.)
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with a salad and dessert.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick the last 4 ingredients. Cool until medium warm. Add cut up strawberries.
Pour into a baked pie shell that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Top with whipped cream.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello and vinegar together and let jell.
Then stir in Miracle Whip, onions, celery and cucumbers.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken and debone it (save the broth).
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Melt butter in skillet and saute chopped bell peppers and onions.
Add tomatoes, soup and spices to taste to mixture and let boil.
In a casserole dish, layer noodles, chicken, sauce and grated cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Form into roll.
Bake at 400°.

title: microwave scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in 1-quart casserole dish; microwave at High for 1/2 minute until melted.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually stir in milk; microwave at High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring every 3 minutes.
Stir in potatoes and onion.
Cover. Microwave at High for 17 to 19 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbles.
Serve with crackers.

title: aunt ethel's cobbler(modified for speed)
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter while oven is preheating to 350°.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and milk. Pour over butter in pan.
Spoon pie filling over batter staying 1-inch away from sides of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dog treats
directions: Pour water into a large bowl.
Add bouillon cubes and crush with fork.
Stir in yeast and let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended.
Sprinkle a little additional flour onto cutting board.
Take 1/3 of the dough and work into ball shape.
Using rolling pin, flatten ball about 1/4-inch thick.
If dough is too sticky, add a little more flour. Cut dough into shapes with cookie cutters or a dull knife.
Use spatula to put biscuits onto a cookie sheet.

title: casserole dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients, except flour.
Mix well.
Stir in yeast mixture. Gradually add flour, beating by hand, to form a stiff dough. Place in well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover; let rise for 50 to 60 minutes.
Punch down; let rise again for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: deluxe baked chicken
directions: Place halves in a shallow baking dish.
Blend together sour cream, onion flakes, lemon juice, salt and paprika.
Spoon over chicken breasts.
Cover with finely crumbled stuffing mix (don't overload).
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: spanish pot roast
directions: Brown meat in 1/4 cup dressing.
Add remaining dressing and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Add onions, potatoes and olives.
Continue simmering 45 minutes until meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter.
Gradually add the remaining water to flour, stirring until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to hot liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve with meat and vegetables or pour over meat and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hamburger corn-pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in melted shortening.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour into a greased casserole;
Top with corn bread batter and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dirt cake
directions: Make pudding with 3 1/2 c. cold milk.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of the crushed Oreos.
Spoon into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle the remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Broil chicken, cut into bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, onions, cheese, garlic salt, chili powder and tomatoes (mashed). Soften tortillas in chicken stock.
Line baking dish with tortillas.
Add chicken mixture.
Pour 2 cans chicken soup over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: file and okra seafood gumbo(serves 10)
directions: In a large soup or stew pot over medium heat, saute the peeled shrimp in vegetable oil (season the shrimp well with salt and pepper before cooking).
When cooked, remove from pot.
Be sure not to overcook.
Saute the already steamed or boiled peeled crabs and claws in the same oil.
Remove from pot after about 1 minute of cooking.
Next, make a roux.
Brown the flour in the vegetable oil.
Watch closely not to burn.
Keep stirring.
Add the chopped onions and bell pepper (keep some of the green onions for garnish when serving).
Saute several minutes until the onions and bell peppers are very soft.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, crumbs, tomato juice and seasonings.
Stir in beef.
Mix well.
Pat meat into a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices atop of meat.
Sprinkle shredded cheese from short end. Roll meat; seal edges.
Put seam down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, then arrange cheese wedges on top of roll.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread on bottom of 13 x 9 or 11 x 9 dish. Layer sausage and then cheese. Pour eggs on top. Add Pet milk. Refrigerate overnight. Take out and let stand to room temperature. Cook at 350° until done.

title: candy
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: spicy cookies
directions: Cream together butter and
sugar;
add
egg
yolk, beat well. Sift together flour
and
cinnamon.
Gradually
add
to cream mixture, stirring well.
Spread
dough evenly in a jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch).
Beat egg white slightly.
Brush over top surface with finger tips.
Sprinkle
nuts
over
dough and press in.
Bake in very slow
oven
for 1 hour.
While cookies are warm, cut into 4
lengthwise and then cut 6 crosswise.
Cut each piece in half diagonally, makes 48 triangles.

title: dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Add more dill if desired.

title: orange peel bread
directions: Put peel of 3 oranges in cold water to cover.
Boil 1/2 hour. Drain.
Repeat twice.
Cool enough to handle.
Scoop while out with spoon.
Cut peel fine.
Make syrup of 3/4 cup sugar and 3/8 cup water.
When dissolved, drop in peel and cook until peel is transparent and syrup is almost absorbed (3/4 of a hour, more or less). Mix in order given.
Add orange peel dredged with flour. Bake in greased and floured pan, about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Stir in oats, soda and salt; blend well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Dough will be stiff.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into large tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Flake salmon in a mixing bowl.
Put in eggs after beating well with rotary eggbeater.
Add flour to mixture and stir until well mixed.
Dissolve baking soda in buttermilk and add to salmon mixture.
Drop from a spoon into hot fat.
Cook until brown on each side.

title: crab stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in medium bowl. Add crab and mix in thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead.) Cover and chill.

title: walter's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, creamed corn and bacon drippings.
Set aside.
Saute meat and onion.
Place on paper towel to absorb any excess grease.
Grease large black iron skillet.
Heat.
Sprinkle a very thin layer of meal in skillet and let it brown slightly.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread evenly in a 9 x 12-inch pan crushed pineapple.
Put cherry pie filling over pineapple.
Put nuts over pie filling. Mix cake mix as box directs and pour over all.
Slice butter thin and arrange over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Combine cooled tortellini with broccoli flowerets, cheese (cut in bite size pieces), red Spanish onion (cut in rings) and drained olives.
Pour Ranch dressing on top and toss lightly.
Line a salad bowl with lettuce leaves and place salad mixture on lettuce. Garnish with Bac*Os and tomato wedges.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Steam ground beef with 1 cup water.
Cook 3 to 4 cups macaroni, Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato juice and mushroom soup.
Cube 3/4 log of Velveeta cheese.
Add to mixture.
Mix all together. Top with remaining Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and bubbly.

title: violet's english drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs and cold coffee.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients.
Add raisins and mix well.
Add nuts last, if desired.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° after dropping by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet, greased.

title: salsa
directions: Bring to boil in stainless steel saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Can or eat fresh.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: frango mints
directions: Melt chocolate chips; let
cool.
In a bowl add 1/2 cup butter, sifted powdered sugar
(maybe
a
little
more so will stand up good), 2
eggs, vanilla and peppermint extract.
Beat real good by hand until thick enough to drop by spoon on waxed paper.
May put through cake decorator tube.

title: seven course casserole
directions: Mix 1 can of soup and 1 can of water in a casserole dish. Make layers of sliced potatoes, peppers, onions and ground meat until all ingredients are used.
Top with the other can of soup and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, Velveeta, Cheddar cheese and eggs in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add cooked macaroni; fold in thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken thighs with skin removed
directions: Brush each thigh with small amount of hot pepper sauce. Sprinkle with garlic powder and Mrs. Dash salt substitute.
Best if grilled.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/4 cup water for 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate with cinnamon and sweetener.
Add milk and water slowly.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla; cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, add nuts; turn into cold pan.
When firm, cut into pieces.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, vegetable oil and eggs in large bowl. Stir in butterscotch chips and nuts, if using. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set. Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: banana and peanut butter snack spud
directions: Cut the potatoes in halves; remove pulp.
Place pulp in bowl and mash.
Combine peanut butter, mashed bananas, milk and spices. Mix with electric mixer until very smooth.
Spoon mixture into the potato shells.
Sprinkle on nutmeg or cinnamon before serving.

title: chicken soup(1888)
directions: Cut up chicken and break the bones. Cook until very tender in 3-quarts of water.
Add water as it boils away so that when done, there will be 3 quarts of soup.
Boil very slowly and when done, remove the meat and bones from the kettle.
Pour the soup into an earthen dish and let stand until cold. Remove every particle of fat from stock. Pour into a saucepan and set on stove. Have ready 1/2 cup rice and add to soup.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Mix all together until eggs are blended with other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix cream of chicken soup with milk, water and cheese.
Stir instant rice and chopped onion into drained broccoli.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir, then let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash, cut in small pieces; cook in small amount of water until tender; drain thoroughly.
Mash and add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake in 1-quart greased casserole dish for 30 minutes in medium hot oven at 350°
Can grate some cheese.
Add to mixture.

title: frankie's banana pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Mix flour (or cornstarch) together.
When milk comes to a slight bubble, stir in flour and 1 cup sugar.
Continue to stir while thickening.
After sauce thickens, stir 2 tablespoons of sauce with 2 egg yolks, then add this to sauce. Add vanilla to sauce.
Place in layers:
vanilla wafers, bananas and sauce.
Repeat.
Top with meringue made from 2 egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brown.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix meat, egg, onion, rice, milk and salt together.
Cut core from cabbage, place cabbage in hot water to separate leaves. Place a small amount of mixture into leaves and secure with a toothpick.
Lay a few leaves in the bottom of a pan, place rolls on them, and top rolls with a few more leaves.
Add soup and water over that.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours to 3 hours.

title: fruitcake balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Add to first mixture.
Add nuts and fruits. Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken chow cashew
directions: Combine chicken, 2 cans noodles, soup, broth, onion and celery.
Top with 1 can chow mein noodles and cashew nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Place ingredients in order listed in a large greased pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad (no. 1)
directions: Mix pineapple, pudding and coconut in bowl and then chill. Then mix in whipped cream and marshmallows.

title: aunt patsy's chili beans(crockpot style)
directions: Wash beans well, place in crockpot with water, salsa & onion. Cook overnight on low.
The next morning add meat in pot and cook on low until dinnertime.
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 6.

title: old-fashioned 3 layer banana cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream lard, sugar and eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients with 1 cup of buttermilk.
Add shortening to the mixture; stir until well blended.
Add mashed bananas and nuts.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: butter jumbles cookies(cut outs)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg and milk.
Add flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Roll out and cut. Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: tortuous tamale pie
directions: Cook onion, pepper and beef in large deep skillet until beef is lightly brown.
Add tomato sauce, corn,
olives, garlic and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted. Pour into greased 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with Cornmeal Topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, sugar and crushed pretzels.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker creme torte
directions: Line bottom of an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan with one layer of whole graham crackers.
Mix the 2 packages of instant pudding with the 3 cups milk. Fold Cool Whip into the pudding. Spread half of this mixture on top of crackers in the pan. Add another layer of graham crackers.
Put remaining pudding on top and add a third layer of crackers.

title: zella's banana fruit bread
directions: Boil raisins in a little water and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add mashed bananas.
Fold in flour, soda and salt.
Last, stir in the chopped apple, raisins and nutmeats.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
This makes 3 small bread pans of bread.

title: make ahead enchilada casserole
directions: Mix monterey cheese, 1 cup cheddar cheese, onion, sour cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Set aside.

title: san francisco's little joe's tomato sauce
directions: It is not necessary to saute any item in this recipe.

Combine the tomatoes, chicken broth, celery, onions, oregano, rosemary, bay leaves, basil, garlic, black pepper, salt and olive oil. Bring all ingredients to a boil for 2 to 4 hours. Thicken with the dissolved cornstarch.
Serve over pasta of your choice.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
You can also add meat or sausage of your choice to the sauce. This sauce can be bottled and frozen for later use.
Serves 8 to 10 persons.

title: chocolate butterscotch scotches
directions: Bring
to
a boil sugar and corn syrup.
Stir in peanut butter and
Rice	Krispies.
Press into oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips over double boiler	or
in microwave.
Spread over Krispies mixture.	Cut into
2 x 1-inch bars while still warm.
Chill in refrigerator for a few minutes to set chocolate.

title: bran muffins by the gallon
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil. Batter will keep in the refrigerator for 6 weeks and can be baked as needed.
Or I prefer making up the muffins and putting them in the freezer.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350° in muffin tins or use Pam or paper liners.
